<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><gpx xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xmlns:groundspeak="http://www.groundspeak.com/cache/1/0/1" xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" version="1.0" creator="Groundspeak, Inc.All Rights Reserved.http://www.groundspeak.com" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.topografix.com/GPX/1/0 http://www.topografix.com/GPX/1/0/gpx.xsd http://www.groundspeak.com/cache/1/0/1 http://www.groundspeak.com/cache/1/0/1/cache.xsd" xmlns="http://www.topografix.com/GPX/1/0"><name>Cache Listing Generated from Geocaching.com</name><desc>This is an individual cache generated from Geocaching.com</desc><email>contact@geocaching.com</email><url>http://www.geocaching.com</url><urlname>Geocaching - High Tech Treasure Hunting</urlname><time>2026-06-02T13:04:03.517067Z</time><keywords>cache, geocache</keywords><wpt lat="33.623767" lon="-86.60125"><time>2001-01-02T00:00:00</time><name>GC126</name><desc>Trussville Civitan - Alabama's First Cache by WheresDiB</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC126</url><urlname>Trussville Civitan - Alabama's First Cache</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="294" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Trussville Civitan - Alabama's First Cache</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>WheresDiB</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="304530">WheresDiB</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="1">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="7" inc="1">Takes less than one hour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="40" inc="1">Stealth required</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="30" inc="1">Picnic tables nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="17" inc="1">Poisonous plants</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="39" inc="1">Thorns</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>3.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>2</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Alabama</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>Trussville Civitan Park.
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>The first Cache in the Grand ol' State of Alabama, and only the 294th cache ever listed on geocaching.com. It was originally hidden by WJ ( http://bit.ly/WN4zxv ) has been maintained over the years by Bubbacache, TheAlabamaRambler, and now by Wheresdib and the Dibcrew. The cache is located just outside the Trussville Civitan Park near the foundation remains of the early-1900s Jefferson County Prison Work Camp. Update 11/17/25 - due to construction, there is no close space to park an RV nearby. Please plan to park your larger vehicles elsewhere and make alternate plans before attempting to find this cache. The City Hall parking lot is currently inaccessible. UPDATE 5/26/20 new larger ammo can in place inside a log nearby the stump which has rotted away. UPDATE 4/1/18 After almost 5 years, the cache is an ammo can again Update 7/29/17 Civitan Park is now open. You can park south of the cache on Parkway Drive at the veterans memorial obliesk near the cache. Enter the woods just east of the fence, stay east and follow the path north past the first two foundations. The cache is inside a trunk. Please cover the cache back well, we’ve lost several ammo cans here. ALTERNATIVELY you can park north of the cache at the Parking coordinates at Masonic Park on Park Place. There is a trail to the cache just beyond the public works but on city property between Masonic and Civitan Parks. You WILL more than likely get barked at, but the dogs are usually in their fences and are tail waggers. Stay in front of the public works and continue until you reach the back side of residential fences. Continue south along the fence line until you reach the coordinates which are reportedly 70' north of the container. NOTE: There is no parking for larger vehicles at either the Veteran's Memorial or the Masonic Park or anywhere along Highway 11 downtown within a mile of the cache in either direction. Please research the area before arriving if you are in an RV or pulling a trailer etc. 
</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Under log</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1364013468"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-28T07:34:27</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="6478470">Sweet Tides Crew</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Day 2 of the MA road trip - stopped for the night without getting a cache on day 1. We drove 670 miles yesterday.

It was a beautiful day to find Alabama’s oldest before the long drive to Shenandoah National Park. The monument here was wrapped in red, white and blue ribbons. A beautiful tribute.

Thank you for keeping this one going!
TFTC 
Sweet Tides Crew</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363597788"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-25T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1271259">NitiFlex</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Vacanze USA 2026 !!!
Come ogni anno eccomi nuovamente in partenza per il mio paese preferito.
Quest'anno ho una compagna di viaggio di livello "stratosferico", l'unica che abbia valutato la mia proposta interessante "after8". Sono ormai 3 anni abbondanti che inseguo le vecchie cache, voglio collezionare Jasmer. Purtroppo per problemi familiari non ho potuto supportare Laura le ultime 3 settimane e il viaggio ha rischiato di saltare ...
Un importante capitolo della mia vita si è concluso ma ora è il momento di cercare un pò di relax.
Percorreremo gli USA da est a ovest, da Atlanta a Phoenix, poche cache salvate nella lista ma di un livello importante.
Giorno 1:
Finisco di lavorare verso le 14.30 e in un'oretta mi ritrovo già in auto sull'e45 alla volta di Roma. Laura è al lavoro fino a tardi ma arriviamo quasi insieme a casa sua. Ottima cenetta e poi una bella passeggiata alla ricerca di una gelateria con cache lungo il tragitto.
Giorno 2 :
Ben poco da dire su questa giornata dedicata al viaggio, termina cmq poco prima di mezzanotte ma con tutto pronto per l'indomani....
Facciamo una Virtual in aeroporto per sentirci in vacanza.
Il meteo è pessimo in quanto diluvia con fulmini e tuoni ma soprattutto mette così per tutti i prossimi giorni...
Giorno 3 :
Alle 5.00 di mattina lasciamo la stanza e per colazione becchiamo una Waffle House che ci rifornisce di energie per la giornata di Geocaching. Non è bel tempo ma almeno non piove. Perdiamo 1 ora per un gennaio 2001 che non troviamo.... che delusione....
Per fortuna il resto della giornata fila liscio, anche troppo visto una mia caduta che mi ha tolto il fiato per 1 minuto, chissa domani come starò 😭.
Giorno 4 :
Secondo giorno di caccia alle oldy, oggi facciamo una puntatina in Alabama ma poi concluderemo la giornata ad Atlanta, sicuramente meno camminate ma molta più auto !!!
About this cache :
Cache più vecchia dello stato !!! 
Tanta roba anche se per un soffio non è un 2000.....
Davvero comoda, si parcheggia e dopo una breve passeggiata stiamo già loggando. 
Qui una commemorazione ci ricorda che oggi 25 maggio è il giorno della Memoria e io posso aggiungere che in Italia si festeggia il compleanno del mio Amico Dr. Matteo Laghi, auguri !!!
Sei il Number 1 !!
Thanks Owner</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363532411"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-25T10:30:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="8847997">after8</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">It is Memorial Day and a lady felt sick, so ambulances and firefighters trucks drive into the parking while we can find the cache undisturbed. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363035524"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-23T22:06:43</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="30920028">mathmanbill</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">OCW JoeBum on a roadtrip based around ATL for four days. Hitting up some oldest state caches and other interesting ones. 

Nice quick state oldie to add to the list!  TFTC. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1362932243"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-23T13:02:31</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="3588517">JoeBum</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">On a 2026 caching trip with mathmanbill. We’ve done kayaks, backpacking, but this year we are working on several state’s oldest. Alabama was our first of 4 that we will collect on this trip. Nice short walk to GZ. Thanks for maintaining this old one.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="57.060767" lon="-135.212617"><time>2000-09-29T00:00:00</time><name>GC68</name><desc>Centurion Guards by Gary &amp; Greg Short</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC68</url><urlname>Centurion Guards</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="104" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Centurion Guards</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Gary &amp; Greg Short</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="1688088">gshort</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Small</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="1" inc="1">Dogs</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="13" inc="1">Available 24/7</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="7" inc="1">Takes less than one hour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="38" inc="1">Campfires</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="15" inc="1">Available in winter</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>2</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>2</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Alaska</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>This cache has had the regular access trail closed due to some construction. I am happy to tell you it is back to its old condition. All is good for hunting. Have a great hunt.</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>I am thrilled to be the first to place a GeoCache in Alaska.
Considering the size of our state that's paramount to being the
first to place a cache west of the Mississippi River. The cache has
been placed in the Alexander Archipelagos on Baranof Island near
the community of Sitka. Since we have only twelve miles of road
that'll limit the driving. Start your quest at the Sawmill Creek
Campground. Cross the footbridge over the creek and your odyssey
commences. This is a level #1 walk of no more than a half mile.
Since the only open ground around Sitka is the airport. You are in a
dense forested area. Trees over a hundred feet surround you. Your
GPS may have trouble getting a lock due to the size of the trees
and the effects of the tight canyon. The cache is in a red 30oz Nalgene water bottle. Search high and search low,
negates the goal you aspire, In between is the way to go, Head
level and no higher. Happy hunting.
Gary</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Root clump, nurse tree, eye level, red, hanging.</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1363632327"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-25T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2492813">RockWrangler</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Sitka day!!! 

Today the cruse ship arrived in Sitka. We decided to start the day with the longer of the hikes for the 2 2000’s caches or so we thought…. Got the first one down and arrived at the second to realize it was now going  to be a 3.85 mile hike…. The gate was closed…. Any way after that hike we went to the raptor center and fortress of the bear and ended the day with a little more caching and a little more shopping!! TFTC!! </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363320466"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-24T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="3136658">3omahakids</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">We will be on a cruise ship and stopping in Sitka on June 24.  We are trying to figure out a way to get this one while we're there.  We have an excursion at 1pm so have from 930-1230 to go get it.  Anybody that will be also be there that day and want to team up on a car rental or know of a better way to get it please contact me and let me know.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1360567174"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-11T12:21:50</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="46346307">DrewskiAndFAM</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">So incredible to get the oldest cache in Alaska with my daughter from Australia in the addallfam.   I am from mn.   We did lots of research and learned so much.   The key is you are going to the campground....not where Google Maps takes you.   We were on a cruise and rented a car and with the gate being closed it was an2 mile walk to the cache.   Well worth it with gorgeous water falls.   And a couple of other cache opportunities.   Alternatively you could take transport to the fortress of the bear sanctuary and walk from there.   We had bear spray for the hike but didn't need it....still glad we had it and we also played music on our phone (tip from a local) and also talked or sang mostly continually.   So very worth it!   </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1360618110"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-11T12:20:51</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="49326726">addallfam</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Fortunate to have found the oldest cache in AK with Drewskiandfam! Gorgeous hike along waterfalls and moss covered trees. The route we took was closer to a 2 mile hike in from the closed gate at the start of the road to the campground. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1359806299"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-08T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="6160211">lwestbroetje</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">I'll be there in September and would love to get this oldie. However being on a cruise ship I'm concerned about the time. Well see!!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="33.53008333333333" lon="-111.58405"><time>2000-09-09T00:00:00</time><name>GC57</name><desc>Geocache by Dan Rich</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC57</url><urlname>Geocache</urlname><sym>Geocache Found</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="87" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Geocache</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Dan Rich</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="25">TEAM SNAKEBUSTERS</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Not chosen</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes /><groundspeak:difficulty>2</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Arizona</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>It is near the salt river recreation area off the Bush Highway. The container 
is a small ammo can. This is open desert bring lots of water. A compass will 
be useful once you find the cache site.</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description /><groundspeak:encoded_hints /><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1364848050"><groundspeak:date>2026-06-01T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1733971">streudelz1222</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">I'm visiting the Phoenix area for a conference, so of course I'm going to grab some of the oldies in the area.  I got up early to make the hour drive here and arrived a little after sunrise.  There was a ranger closing the gate but luckily I was planning on hoofing it all the way rather than trying to drive my rental car on the dirt road.  I double checked with her that I was good to go - she was simply closing the gate so wild horses don't go on the main road!  I chose the sandy trail west of the dirt road as it was a bit more of a direct route and required less off-trail bushwhacking to get to this one.  It was about a mile and a half each way to this one, and it took me about an hour and a half round trip.  I enjoyed the views and enjoyed the early morning hike to beat the heat.  Thank you for keeping this one going for over 25 years!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364673851"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-31T10:31:47</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1277554">ravenraven</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">That is quite a Desert trek. Curious why originally it was placed here.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364078766"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-28T12:23:33</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="7481537">Y2K'</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">A good little trek out here with CongoRongo, glad to get this oldie. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364078422"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-28T12:22:17</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="11172256">Clongo_Rongo</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Log to follow </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364108870"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-28T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2170295">DR.D.</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Since some cachers have had questions, I'll re-post this update. N gate for Bulldog Canyon. N 33° 33.058 W 111° 34.895 You can order a permit from, Bulldog Canyon permit at Mesa Ranger Station 5140 E. Ingram Street Mesa, AZ 85205. Phone (480) 610-3300 Fax (480) 610 3346 or online at https://www.recreation.gov/vehiclepermits/3332401  The road is a little bumpy, but you can make it with a little ground clearance. If you walk or drive in, use N 33° 31.912 W 111° 34.426 as your take off point from the road. From there, head towards GC7GJ93 West towards 57. From there, head towards GCAQHN6 The Rising #5. After that GC57 is in your sights. As you approach, Take the left side of the wash. There is a small trail that leads down and back up the other side towards GZ. Carry lots of water. Hope this helps. I have been care-taking this cache for several years and have all WP's. If you have any questions, message me. Cache-On!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1237104628"><groundspeak:date>2024-05-27T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2089726">travelingGeek</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Nice hike in, but at a faster pace than I like, especially in the desert.  The line of cars on the highway for Memorial Day river fun was a lot longer than we had expected and made us worry about getting to the airport on time.  We went the "long way" from the gate and made it out pretty quickly.  Whew!

Final day of our Geo Woodstock trip and we’re still zipping around finding caches.  I had the pleasure of caching with TAZ427 and Av8MxGrl again. The goal today was to get to GC57 and then to the airport!

Thanks to all the cache owners that made all our fun today possible!

</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="36.337972" lon="-92.38035"><time>2000-06-27T00:00:00</time><name>GC1B</name><desc>Gorilla Stash by Ed Normandy</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC1B</url><urlname>Gorilla Stash</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="27" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Gorilla Stash</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Ed Normandy</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="4471">ednormandy</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="24" inc="1">Wheelchair accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="1">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="1" inc="1">Dogs</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="13" inc="0">Available 24/7</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="7" inc="1">Takes less than one hour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="53" inc="1">Park and grab</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="65" inc="1">Yard (private residence)</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="32" inc="1">Bicycles</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="63" inc="1">Recommended for tourists</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="59" inc="1">Food nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="33" inc="1">Motorcycles</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="46" inc="0">Trucks/RVs</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="58" inc="1">Fuel nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="15" inc="1">Available in winter</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Arkansas</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>This is the perfect place for exchanging trackables. It has traded almost 4000 items and is well known for that feature.
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>
</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>if buttercup could drool, his cache would be wet.</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1364266361"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-29T21:38:05</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="22628262">marla45</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">9978 current count

Out from Yuma Arizona with a few likeminded friends for GWXXII and ahem, a few other targets.  GC1B   Gorilla Stash
was one of them:

Yes!!! We’ve visited 5 states oldest this trip, and buttercup is my favorite for sure!!!

If answers were required one of us four sent them for all of us.

Nice cache-thanks for placing it here for us to find. Alls well here unless otherwise noted.

Running amok thru 5 states gathering states oldest, counties, challenges and anything else that comes our way. RoxieMama, KoolWaters, Earthikers and of course ParkerSaru are on a journey for both smiles and laughs.Stopping for caches, interesting places and more.

Thanks, ednormandy for the fun! 
May 29, 2026
</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364220842"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-29T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="10356987">JustGeocachingAlong</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Helloooooo from Annapolis, MD! UrbanBlacksmith and I came down this way for an event this morning from Branson. We decided to stay in the area and get Arkansas’ oldest along with some other caches around here. We left 3 travel bugs, took nothing. All is good here. TFTC. 😃

_______________________
