</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>The cache is less than 100 ft off the Bob Trail.</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1364060349"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-28T13:33:24</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="15781996">nremt63</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Tftc tnln Beautiful trail ride thru one of the many hidden gems of Sussex County. Cool find being a local born bred n raised on 302, beaches n scrapple. 
And if you see any trash along the way, please help the hard working staff of Trap Pond State Park who keep this park beautiful and pick it up. ❤️</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1362635222"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-22T10:29:14</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2508723">fondue4two</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Thank you for keeping this year 2000 geocache alive. 
after paying the $10 fee for out-of-state vehicle, we parked in the parking lot closest to the geocache 

We arrived at Ground Zero at 10:29 after driving over from Bethany Beach this morning. We parked the Geo Mobile and walked the very flat and wide crushed gravel trail about .8 miles to Ground Zero. 

We only saw a handful of people, but they were very close to the parking lot. We grabbed one trackable, and left two. 
Greetings from Madison, Wisconsin 
😀❤️🫕🥳🥳🥳🥳🥳🥳</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1362391101"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-20T22:17:04</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="8138433">NeenahGeo</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Made our way here to get another oldest cache in a state, hot day and a nice walk after a lot of driving, cache found.  Dropped off a travel bug.  TFTC</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1361249823"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-15T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="444536">charliewhiskey</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">mr. charliewhiskey and I came out from Oregon to visit for a few days on our way to visit family and attend a 50th class reunion. I was undecided about going after this one.  It was quite a way out of our area of operations.  But hey - what's another 120 miles once you've traveled across the US for a chance to get a year 2000 cache. 

It was a lovely day for a walk, and we weren't the only ones to think so.  We shared the trail with other walkers, runners, and dog owners, and were serenaded by birdsong the whole way.  We found the cache right off and it's in great shape.  I tucked in a pathtag.  

Thanks for bringing us to this lovely park and for keeping this grand old cache going.  </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1361215080"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-15T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="3480806">Runnercacher</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">On my way from finishing up the Eastern Shore counties, to visit Math Boy and family in Dover for the weekend. Had a nice hike here in Trap Pond SP! Spotted the hiding place from 100 feet away. 😁 I think this is my 11th state's oldest. Thanks for the fun!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="33.87175" lon="-83.9718"><time>2000-06-03T00:00:00</time><name>GC1D</name><desc>Beaver Cache (the beavers have moved on) by Jim Gooch</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC1D</url><urlname>Beaver Cache (the beavers have moved on)</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="29" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Beaver Cache (the beavers have moved on)</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Jim Gooch</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="4261">Annie!</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Large</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="24" inc="0">Wheelchair accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="1">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="13" inc="0">Available 24/7</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="7" inc="1">Takes less than one hour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="32" inc="1">Bicycles</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="55" inc="1">Short hike (&lt;1 km)</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="33" inc="0">Motorcycles</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="34" inc="0">Quads</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="35" inc="0">Off-road vehicles</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="15" inc="1">Available in winter</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="18" inc="1">Dangerous animals</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="19" inc="1">Ticks</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Georgia</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>It's near Grayson, GA. New (8/19/01) TEN gallon screw top white bucket buried. It floats during heavy rain.
&lt;p&gt;You must park in park in the parking lot and proceed along the outside of fenced areas. Otherwise you will be trespassing. It is hidden on the common area. Be Respectful of those who live here. They have been kind enough to let the cache remain ...&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Do not cross any fences or open any gates.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;ONLY AVAILABLE DURING DAYLIGHT HOURS!!!&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>It's worth the hunt, because the lake is very pretty.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Park here.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;img src="http://img.geocaching.com/cache/e37f2b5d-fc05-4f21-a98a-30ac0ced8ca1.jpg" /&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Happy hunting.&lt;/p&gt;

</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints /><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1363878259"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-27T10:45:10</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1731223">Amante1</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Very happy to find this one, the sun peaked through just as I arrived, so didn’t have to worry about the rain. Traveling from North Carolina trying to pick up old hides for Jasmer.  Thanks so much for maintaining this oldest in Georgia!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363483748"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-25T10:03:34</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="5815145">GreenGirl3</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Found with quarterdad, thanks for the cache and keeping it maintained! </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363480566"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-25T09:54:15</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="4511075">quarterdad</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Found with Greengirl3.  Finally finally finished that Jasmer challenge! Thanks for keeping this going! </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363356270"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-24T22:41:38</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="3588517">JoeBum</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Day 2 of an oldie trip with mathmanbill. Today’s goals included Stone Mountain and MoDoc Stash. We had surprisingly great weather for our hike to the top.

Mathmanbill already had this one, but we added it to the list so that I could make the find as well. All good at GZ. Glad to get another oldest!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363355504"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-24T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="5268266">Pine Baron</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">5512. Down from New Jersey with the One More Cache Crew visiting family and doing a little caching. This was one of our (4) biggest targets. The first was visiting my daughter Diace. The other (3) targets were the grand oldies that are all in close proximity to each other, in this region.

With Diace along for the fun, we parked at the prescribed spot and made the short, but nice walk to GZ. I spotted the container from a distance and found it in pristine condition! We all signed the log and traded some. Thanx for keeping this great old one alive for all to enjoy!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="21.392933" lon="-157.90215"><time>2000-07-21T00:00:00</time><name>GC23</name><desc>Geocache by Migoi (adopted by GeoGerms 5/4/2008)</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC23</url><urlname>Geocache</urlname><sym>Geocache Found</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="35" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Geocache</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Migoi (adopted by GeoGerms 5/4/2008)</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="733552">GeoGerms</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes /><groundspeak:difficulty>2</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>2.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Hawaii</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>Easy walk in the woods. Suitable for the whole family. I am basically a lazy person so your off trail scramble is very short and NOT uphill. Please reseal the lid completely when you are done. Thanks. Enjoy the hike.</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>After re-reading some of the logs over the last year I feel compelled to add: NOT UPHILL NOT UPHILL NOT UPHILL NOT UPHILL NOT UPHILL after you leave the trail. If you think you need to be doing an uphill off-trail scramble, take a deep breath, take out one of the original style power bars (the ones with a taffy-like consistency) and keep walking on the trail until you've managed to chew your way through it. Again... NOT UPHILL, NOT UPHILL, NOT UPHILL, NOT UPHILL.

migoi</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints /><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1364493034"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-30T16:40:21</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="7358360">jtown1190</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Beautiful hike, really muddy though. Wish I would have remembered not needing to climb the hill. Tftc</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363797427"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-26T12:13:53</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="286869">MinotRanger</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Woo hoo!  What a cache.  My 45th state oldest.  It sprinkled on the way in.  Earns a favorite.  </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364117985"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-16T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="317204">Geojeepsters</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Found on a quick hike and two day visit to the Island. Musubi and Dim Sum!   Favorite point here although it was raining and slick </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1360617217"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-12T09:20:50</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="49465352">HotPlantain</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Found it! Bibi &amp; Rylee</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1360498039"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-11T11:32:34</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1130512">Team O'Grady</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">TFTC - lovely lunchtime stroll!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="561147451"><groundspeak:date>2015-12-11T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2089726">travelingGeek</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Great short hike (we didn't do the full loop) to get this cache.  We meet some great people on the trail and had a all around great time.  Thanks for keeping this old timer around for our caching pleasure.

Oh, and don't forget.... NOT UPHILL!

This is my 6th oldest in a state cache (including DC)!

Thanks and Mahalo!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="48.539183" lon="-116.750083"><time>2000-06-17T00:00:00</time><name>GC25</name><desc>Camels Prairie Stash by Moun10Bike, Cindy, Laura and Jasmine</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC25</url><urlname>Camels Prairie Stash</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="37" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Camels Prairie Stash</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Moun10Bike, Cindy, Laura and Jasmine</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="24">Moun10Bike</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Large</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="15" inc="0">Available in winter</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>2</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>3</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Idaho</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>

</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;center&gt;&lt;h2&gt;Idaho's first geocache&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;img src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/gs-geo-images/955f655b-6ffa-41f5-bed5-ba64407c128a.jpg" /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;Aerial view over Camels Prairie (drone image courtesy of &lt;a href="https://www.geocaching.com/p/?guid=b1a8ec40-4bd4-4d4a-b95d-2fa51cf1815f" target="_blank"&gt;kootenay pirates&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/center&gt;

&lt;center&gt;
&lt;table style="background-color:#d4f4d4;width:85%;max-width:700px;border-collapse:collapse;margin:20px auto;border:1px solid #a0d0a0;"&gt;
  &lt;tr&gt;
    &lt;td style="padding:12px 15px;font-weight:bold;width:35%;border-bottom:1px solid #a0d0a0;"&gt;Season:&lt;/td&gt;
    &lt;td style="padding:12px 15px;border-bottom:1px solid #a0d0a0;"&gt;Typically &lt;b&gt;early June through late October&lt;/b&gt; (snow)&lt;/td&gt;
  &lt;/tr&gt;
  &lt;tr&gt;
    &lt;td style="padding:12px 15px;font-weight:bold;border-bottom:1px solid #a0d0a0;"&gt;Driving distance:&lt;/td&gt;
    &lt;td style="padding:12px 15px;border-bottom:1px solid #a0d0a0;"&gt;If you have a high-clearance vehicle that can make it up to the end of the rough and rutted Camels Prairie Road, then you can drive to within a couple of hundred yards/meters of the cache. This route is about &lt;b&gt;10 miles/6 km&lt;/b&gt; from the pavement of the East Shore Road, with most of that on good quality forest roads. Otherwise, you can park at the lower parking waypoint, which is approximately &lt;b&gt;8.5 miles/13.7 km&lt;/b&gt; from pavement.&lt;/td&gt;
  &lt;/tr&gt;
  &lt;tr&gt;
    &lt;td style="padding:12px 15px;font-weight:bold;border-bottom:1px solid #a0d0a0;"&gt;Hiking distance:&lt;/td&gt;
    &lt;td style="padding:12px 15px;"&gt;Just &lt;b&gt;a couple of hundred yards/meters&lt;/b&gt; if you can drive up to the end of the Camels Prairie Road, or about &lt;b&gt;1.4 miles/2.3 km&lt;/b&gt; from the lower parking waypoint.&lt;/td&gt;
  &lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/center&gt;

&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;b&gt;Original description:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/i&gt;
&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This stash is located near Priest Lake in the panhandle. It is a 5-gallon white bucket sunk into the ground with about 2 inches of the rim showing, and a lid labeled "GPS Stash." The stash site is located just off of a passable road near the summit, but those without a high-clearance/4x4 vehicle may want to park at the junction 1-1/4 miles below the stash site and walk the remaining distance. Overall, the stash is located about 10 miles off of the pavement.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Enjoy the hunt, and the spectacular views!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I have posted the route up to the cache from pavement on my personal Dropbox site in the following formats:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;ul&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.dropbox.com/scl/fi/gxa70diui2xgrclr2pkc1/Route-to-Camels-Prairie.gpx?rlkey=k0gdwqi9wtjs0aw5kxmteri1c&amp;amp;st=yocwc8l1&amp;amp;dl=0" target="_blank"&gt;GPX track&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.dropbox.com/scl/fi/yvyi9g8bgok2ccd079c5s/Route-to-Camels-Prairie.kml?rlkey=m6npy6nb8ji6vwtsyfw3o2jjn&amp;amp;st=87txbuza&amp;amp;dl=0" target="_blank"&gt;KML file&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/&lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.dropbox.com/scl/fi/7g9p1hcwn5debcqf43e3p/Route-to-Camels-Prairie.png?rlkey=jhzojgb6ya0ylwulsfxolzzjy&amp;amp;st=8qjr4pep&amp;amp;dl=0" target="_blank"&gt;Image&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints /><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1341927347"><groundspeak:date>2026-01-15T22:57:17</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="19867539">RenéeCache</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Would someone please be nice enough to send me all of the log entry photos from 8/17/2022?
Thanks</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1332109356"><groundspeak:date>2025-10-28T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="24">Moun10Bike</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">I just finished marking 140 trackables logged into this cache as missing. The majority of these were dropped by a single user back in June. Visitors to the cache following June 28 have reported to me that they found no trackables at all in the cache.

I've tried reaching out to the user who made the bulk drop via both email and the Message Center to ask if by chance the mass drop was an error on their part, but they have unfortunately not responded. I've decided that it was finally time to clean up the cache's inventory.

Several of the trackables that I have marked as missing have since been logged as seen in other locations, so hopefully all or at least most of these are still out there circulating and have just been temporarily waylaid by some mistaken logging.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1332104404"><groundspeak:date>2025-10-28T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="927119">Sagasu</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">.
494 favorites or not, I was skeptical of this being a "safe" cache to park our last white jeep from the minute I saw the retrieve and drop logs promising a safe parking spot. Unlike some of our other jeeps, there is no longer a replacement for this one. Eight years was an ok run....

re:

10/28/2025	Moun10Bike marked it as missing	 	Visit Log
This is an automated message. This Trackable has been marked 'missing' by a cache owner or site administrator. Trackables are marked missing when it is determined that they are no longer located in the cache they are listed in or in the hands of the current holder. Review the most recent logs on this Trackable to learn more information about its current state.

Dropped Off 06/28/2025	Lacknothing placed it in Camels Prairie Stash	Idaho - 1,361.8 miles 	Visit Log
Grab It (Not from a Cache) 11/18/2020	Lacknothing grabbed it	 	Visit Log
Thank you LAD for passing this sweet Jeep onto me. It is a beaut - that is for sure. And I know how Jeeps like to travel - so I will be sure to take some photos of adventures and eventually land this one in a safe location.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1329196737"><groundspeak:date>2025-10-11T16:31:08</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="310103">zmw</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">At the APE block party in August, we decided to start finding the oldies caches. This was our fourth state &amp; probably our last for 2025 since the snow was falling as we made the hike. My hands &amp; feet were cold but we were still able to sign the log before running back down to the car. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1327072579"><groundspeak:date>2025-09-29T17:57:28</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="16637518">geomike49</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">I went on a road trip from Portland to grab three old caches in Idaho and two in Montana.
This was the last cache on my list.  

It was a long, winding drive up the hill and I was happy the road was in such great shape for most of the climb. At the last "go left" waypount, I opted to leave my vehicle behind and continue on foot.  I would have driven up that last road in a rented Wrangler or truck and had no problems, but it looked a bit sporty for my fairly new Subaru Ascent.  

At the GZ, I looked around a bit before finally spotting the geopile concealing the cache.  Thanks for keeping this old cache going!
</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="42.08971666666667" lon="-88.22465"><time>2000-05-13T00:00:00</time><name>GC28</name><desc>Beverly by Robert Reindl</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC28</url><urlname>Beverly</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="40" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Beverly</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Robert Reindl</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="13">robamy</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="15" inc="1">Available in winter</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="50" inc="1">May require cross country skis</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="17" inc="1">Poisonous plants</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="39" inc="1">Thorns</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>2</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>2</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Illinois</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>The difficulty and terrain have a rating of ~1.5 because there are so many interesting ways to approach the Geocache. It can be easy and/or difficult depending on many factors (you will see).&lt;br /&gt;
When in doubt bring your boots!&lt;br /&gt;
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>This is a beautiful area for a hike with friends and family! You will see lots of trees, diverse land features and some elevation (something we don’t see much of in the Chicagoland area).&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
A compass may be helpful when the canopy is thicker. Take your time and explore the area. You will find plenty of interesting artifacts amongst the vegetation.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Long pants, boots, compass and bug spray are most likely needed for this one! Please note there is Poison Ivy in the area.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Please help keep our parks beautiful and pack out some trash on your way out.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Note: There is private property in the area, which is identified by signs. Not all borders are marked clearly.
</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Start here N 42 04.954’ W88 13.851’ (WGS-84). 
Last ~500 feet are off trail.</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1364462452"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-30T16:00:43</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="48626940">nathor98</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Glad to add the longest running cache in IL to our finds! Ground zero is a fun trek, and some fun swag/trackables to discover too. Tftc! </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364461439"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-30T15:55:58</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="54758467">claybutz</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Tftc</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364407235"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-30T12:04:11</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="934052">mikbalt</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Today we arrived in Chicago from Houston to spend about 9 days of fun and relaxation where we will visit several museums and try the delicious cuisine and end with Pokemon Go Fest 2026! My first goal of the trip was to find the third oldest geocache in the world, which has been on my geocache to do list for quite some time. I am on this trip with all non cachers, so I had to convince everyone to talk a pleasant walk in the park after a delicious breakfast at Benedicts eggs and more. Eve be was on board with the walk, so we made the short trip. My daughter and I were the one only two willing to venture off trail. There was an obvious geotrail and it was a very easy (barely a) bushwack. We spotted the cache and signed the log. Thank you for maintaining this legendary cache. TFTC and favorite point!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364263912"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-29T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="311411">Freunden</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">This was the reason we decided to cache in IL today.  So happy to have found the cache after the hike and bushwacking.  Signed log as F&amp;T.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364226108"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-29T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="234571">Temacon</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">What a nice park!  Visiting from Iowa. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="39.27795" lon="-100.943683"><time>2000-05-11T00:00:00</time><name>GC30</name><desc>Mingo by The Kansas Stasher</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC30</url><urlname>Mingo</urlname><sym>Geocache Found</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="48" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Mingo</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>The Kansas Stasher</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="20">Kansas Stasher</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="1">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="1" inc="1">Dogs</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="13" inc="1">Available 24/7</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="7" inc="1">Takes less than one hour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="32" inc="1">Bicycles</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="40" inc="1">Stealth required</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="33" inc="1">Motorcycles</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Kansas</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>Quick stop for a long trip.</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>A 6" round container buried in the ground.  Only the lid is exposed.

Added August 29, 2004:
Over the last couple of years people have been saying that this is the oldest still active cache. (see http://forums.groundspeak.com/GC/index.php?showtopic=48657 for more discussion.) I know for sure that it was the 7th ever created and the 1st in Kansas.  I would like to thank everyone who has stopped and visited so far.  And let's keep it going for a long, long time.</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints /><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1364890581"><groundspeak:date>2026-06-01T15:14:46</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="55535592">kristintowns</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Kid loved it! First one </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364868291"><groundspeak:date>2026-06-01T13:18:42</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="12100188">GeoNinja54</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Randomly saw this on the map as I was driving by.  What a find. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364917211"><groundspeak:date>2026-06-01T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="387551">Hummingbird &amp; Blue Jay</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Easy PNG. cache in great shape. FP for diligently preserving this piece of geocaching lore. Great container too ! We have been looking forward to logging this one for quite a while.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364844524"><groundspeak:date>2026-06-01T11:21:33</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="4276827">Dylan Bruney</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">So glad it's still here 26 years later! Awesome road trip stop.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364832510"><groundspeak:date>2026-06-01T09:59:22</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="50798604">RutherfordBach</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">TFTC! KS2MT Roadtrip Cache #1; June Streak Challenge Day 1

Although our family has lived in Kansas for 11 years, we never knew about Mingo or its significance to Geocaching. My brother and I set up our accounts about 2 years ago, but we only really got seriously into geocaching this January, while at college in Florida. 

At a small event in Lake Mary, FL, a veteran geocacher of many years informed us that one of the most significant caches is in Kansas of all places. However, at this same time, my family was making preparations to move out of state. This left me with a nagging question—would I be able to find Mingo before moving back to my home state of Montana? For a while, I was convinced the answer was no. 

However, our route this morning just happened to go by Mingo. Hooray! Sadly, my brother was not with me, but hopefully he too can find it soon. 

Left one of my little turtles and awarded a favorite point for this historic cache. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363361865"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-24T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2089726">travelingGeek</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">What an amazing trip this has been!
I've been going to woodstocks for over a decade but this was the first Geo road trip my wife joined me on!   It's been a treat sharing the fun with her and her sister.
To also manage to finally get to Mingo was icing on top!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="38.277333" lon="-85.563583"><time>2001-03-01T00:00:00</time><name>GC39E</name><desc>Tom Sawyer by rlcoffey</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC39E</url><urlname>Tom Sawyer</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="926" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Tom Sawyer</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>rlcoffey</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="2454">rlcoffey</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="1">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="7" inc="1">Takes less than one hour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="63" inc="1">Recommended for tourists</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Kentucky</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>Located in E.P. "Tom" Sawyer State Park. Very flat, cache is not
far off trail.</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>Cache is a rubbermaid container, wont hold anything much bigger
than a cd. I placed in it a log book, a Joe Walsh CD, a
thermometer/minicompass combo, and a deck of cards. 
&lt;p&gt;This cache isnt located near any great vista, but its a nice
trail and might make a good beginner find.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I parked in the main parking lot off Freys Hill Rd. There may be
better places to park.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Update, May 12th: I visited the cache, its still in good shape.
No sign of tracks or trail around cache. Due to growth, you will
have to "bushwack" a little to get to the cache.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Update June 23rd: I took some items out to open up some space in
the cache. They will go into a new cache I will be placing in the
next few weeks. Growth is much higher than it was in May, its waist
high now. Try to be careful when tromping to the cache.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Update Nov 23rd: Cache has been temporarily removed for clean up
of tic-tac goo. Will be back in place by Sunday. Please, dont put
food or candy in the cache, it makes a nasty mess.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Update Nov 25th: Cache is back in place!! I cleaned all the
items in the cache so none are sticky. Cache is even in a brand new
container - exactly the same as the old one, only clean.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Update May 7th, 2004: Cache has been removed for much needed and
overdue repairs. Will be back in place this weekend, I hope.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Update Sep 21, 2004: Replaced cache with ammo box. Cache is
going to be maintained by members of GEOCKY. &lt;/p&gt;</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Behindthetallthingycoveredinbark</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1364868133"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-31T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="287644">abnduo&amp;spawn</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Having gotten the oldest and second oldest cache in Indiana on our way to Michigan for a family reunion, grabbing the oldest and second oldest cache in Michigan, along with grabbing finds in counties that we didn't have lit up on our Michigan and Indiana counties with a find map, we chose a route through Kentucky on our way back home to light up a few more counties for our county finds map in this great state as well!

Having gotten the oldest caches in both Indiana and Michigan, we had to stop in and grab the oldest in Kentucky. This was an insurance find for Jefferson County, it's had to believe our first find in the county was almost 12 years ago here in the county of abn1's birth. Thanks so much for maintaining this grandfather cache!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363953913"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-27T17:44:40</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="8847997">after8</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">
Not too easy to get into the park: 
We had to cross the highway. The path we were aiming to was fenced and the main one was flooded. We jumped over sticks to overpass it. 
Finding the cache was the easiest part. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363955529"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-27T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1271259">NitiFlex</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Vacanze USA 2026 !!!
Come ogni anno eccomi nuovamente in partenza per il mio paese preferito.
Quest'anno ho una compagna di viaggio di livello "stratosferico", l'unica che abbia valutato la mia proposta interessante "after8". Sono ormai 3 anni abbondanti che inseguo le vecchie cache, voglio collezionare Jasmer. Purtroppo per problemi familiari non ho potuto supportare Laura le ultime 3 settimane e il viaggio ha rischiato di saltare ...
Un importante capitolo della mia vita si è concluso ma ora è il momento di cercare un pò di relax.
Percorreremo gli USA da est a ovest, da Atlanta a Phoenix, poche cache salvate nella lista ma di un livello importante.
Giorno 1:
Finisco di lavorare verso le 14.30 e in un'oretta mi ritrovo già in auto sull'e45 alla volta di Roma. Laura è al lavoro fino a tardi ma arriviamo quasi insieme a casa sua. Ottima cenetta e poi una bella passeggiata alla ricerca di una gelateria con cache lungo il tragitto.
Giorno 2 :
Ben poco da dire su questa giornata dedicata al viaggio, termina cmq poco prima di mezzanotte ma con tutto pronto per l'indomani....
Facciamo una Virtual in aeroporto per sentirci in vacanza.
Il meteo è pessimo in quanto diluvia con fulmini e tuoni ma soprattutto mette così per tutti i prossimi giorni...
Giorno 3 :
Alle 5.00 di mattina lasciamo la stanza e per colazione becchiamo una Waffle House che ci rifornisce di energie per la giornata di Geocaching. Non è bel tempo ma almeno non piove. Perdiamo 1 ora per un gennaio 2001 che non troviamo.... che delusione....
Per fortuna il resto della giornata fila liscio, anche troppo visto una mia caduta che mi ha tolto il fiato per 1 minuto, chissa domani come starò 😭.
Giorno 4 :
Secondo giorno di caccia alle oldy, oggi facciamo una puntatina in Alabama ma poi concluderemo la giornata ad Atlanta, sicuramente meno camminate ma molta più auto !!!
Giorno 5 :
Partenza sempre verso le 5.30, oggi la Coordinatrice di Viaggio after8 ha organizzato un bel viaggio in barca per Marooned. Ma prima di questo abbiamo l'unica cache che non potevo mancare e quella per la quale era obbligatorio venire in Georgia, l'ultimo agosto 2000 che mi mancava. Direi che sono il primo italiano a trovarle tutte e 4 !!!
Giorno 6 :
Stamattina in siamo partiti più tardi, tipo le 6.00 Hihihi.
Giornata con poche cache, ci dedichiamo alle "Welcome to" che servono a Laura e non faremo nessun 2000. Sosta per la spesa e tante miglia davanti.
About this cache :
Eccoci alla cache più vecchia del Kentucky's, i sentieri che portano a questa piccolina sono abbastanza allagati ma riusciamo ad aggirare i laghetti.
Punto Favorito Meritato !!!
Thanks Owner</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363811604"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-26T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="382938">incepit</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">A quick find after a walk in the rain, the trail was water logged, but it wouldn;t stop me from reaching this one. Thanks for the fun and the cache.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363234270"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-24T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="5541952">Dean &amp; Chris</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">We added an extra 100 miles to our route just to get this very special cache. We tolerated the heavy downpour and finally made it to GZ. Unfortunately none of the listed trackables were still inside this cache, so we didn't leave ours. Too bad. Still we are very happy to bag Kentucky's oldest geocache. Thank you very much!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="43.621033" lon="-70.213667"><time>2001-01-02T00:00:00</time><name>GC128</name><desc>The Fort Williams Cache by Richard Amirault &gt; kayakerinme &gt; TAT</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC128</url><urlname>The Fort Williams Cache</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="296" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>The Fort Williams Cache</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Richard Amirault &gt; kayakerinme &gt; TAT</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="34942">TAT</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="1">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="1" inc="1">Dogs</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="13" inc="0">Available 24/7</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="7" inc="1">Takes less than one hour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="40" inc="1">Stealth required</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="30" inc="1">Picnic tables nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="28" inc="1">Public restrooms nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="15" inc="0">Available in winter</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Maine</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>Maine's oldest cache located in Fort Williams Park in Cape Elizabeth.
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;cache container is an ammo box.!&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is the first GeoCache in the state of Maine! It was featured on the back of the Maine 2005 geocoin. A 2011 geocoin commemorates the 10th Anniversary of the first cache in Maine.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Fort Williams Park is on the rocky coast of Maine in Cape Elizabeth. Also on the property is the Portland Headlight, one of the most photographed lighthouses in the world. The park is open from dawn until dusk daily. Be aware that the park has many uses and there are some days when a visit might be difficult including Family Fun Day (June), the running of the Beach to Beacon road race (August), and the Labor Day Art Festival.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The cache container is a metal olive drab military ammo box. After 10 years, it was a bit rusty, but well loved. That ammo can went missing and was replaced with a more recent sibling.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;After finding the cache be sure to visit the Lighthouse Gift Shop (in the garage) and the Lighthouse Museum (in the lighthouse building) and check out the great views of Portland Harbor! The park is also a favorite kite flying site.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Note: travel bugs have a habit of going missing from this cache. Better to dip than to leave them, it seems.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>In amongst the rocks.</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1364683955"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-31T14:04:09</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="52356564">Potzy3</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Found w/ Hannesschneider. Good day for finding Maine's oldest cache!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364683675"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-31T14:02:06</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="44354826">HannesSchneider</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">What an honor to have found this today. Didn’t realize Maine’s oldest cache was so close to me! A favorite for me for sure. TFTC and all who have maintained it’s presence </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363956280"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-27T19:54:22</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="37377300">Steinwalker</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Historic Cache, thanks for guiding us here :)</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363885869"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-27T11:31:05</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="44461750">ladyfish96</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">TFTC. Great history</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363886858"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-27T11:30:26</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="11454452">P_E_M</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">With Ladyfish 96 while traveling to Maine.

Very cool to find this historic cache!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="41.9995" lon="-79.99845"><time>2000-09-21T00:00:00</time><name>GC184</name><desc>State Game Lands #109 by Henry Schmitt, Dan Klein</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC184</url><urlname>State Game Lands #109</urlname><sym>Geocache Found</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="388" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>State Game Lands #109</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Henry Schmitt, Dan Klein</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="1923">hschmitt</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="7" inc="1">Takes less than one hour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="15" inc="1">Available in winter</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="22" inc="1">Hunting area</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>2</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>2</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Pennsylvania</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>Near the swampy Confluence 42N 80W in State Game Lands #109, SE of
Erie, PA</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;strong&gt;10th Anniversary Celebration!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
Thanx to everyone who came to join us on the 10th anniversary of
this cache. We had a great time meeting everyone. We'll be posting
pictures of the event for those of you who couldn't make it.&lt;br /&gt;
Original Entry: On our visit to &lt;a href=
"http://www.confluence.org/us/pa/n42w080/index.html"&gt;Confluence 42N
80W&lt;/a&gt; we left a cache nearby. Rather than leave it in the swamp
proper, we left it in the crotch of the 5-trunked maple tree seen
in &lt;a href=
"http://www.confluence.org/us/pa/n42w080/pic5.jpg"&gt;picture #5&lt;/a&gt;.
In addition to the logbook and a pen, we also left a Sendmail
laser/knife and a "Droopy Dog" toy. The cache is fairly easy to
reach, and only requires some bushwacking. However, it's nearby a
swamp and you might want hip-waders if its been raining. This may
have been the first cache in Pennsylvania, but it's taken us 4
months to post it.</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints /><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1364634781"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-31T11:22:24</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="15193104">GMGator17</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Found it thank you </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364414565"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-30T13:33:24</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="468159">cjhanson</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Yay, we did it! One of the main goals of this trip was to find the oldest geocache in Pennsylvania. Not a bad short, walk to the muddy, muddy wet path/trail to GZ. Super glad we both had boot covers along. Found the cache in great shape, signed the log and headed back to the car. Another oldie crossed off our list.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364415725"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-30T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="16271950">grandmabonnie44</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">cjhanson and I got our boots on and headed down the trail to PA'S oldest. Nice to have hip waders so I didn't worry when I started to sink in the muck. Thanks for keeping this oldie alive. TFTC and all the fun</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364253786"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-29T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="79259">BlackstoneVal</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Revisited this oldie and swapped trackable Bigfoot for butterfly coin.
Val and Mar from New England with CMA8</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364239134"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-29T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="135681">Scout338</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">From Central MA.  Working our way back home from GeoWoodstock.  This is the oldest in PA and one of our last Jasmer! Nothing but a muddy dear trail and glad we had our muckers but it was the yellow brick road to us! Replaced with the extact container,  old wet logs inserted  with a new log in a pill container for future cachers. Placement date is our anniversary! We Had to evict a tree frog. Thanks for the fun. Scout338😁</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="554712952"><groundspeak:date>2015-11-01T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2089726">travelingGeek</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">I've had my eye on this one for a long time.  I've been within an hour of it several times, and early in my caching days, I was practically on top of it but hadn't been clued into the "oldest active cache" obsession yet.

I was visiting Jamestown NY for a special mass for my parents.  After mass me and a dozen or so muggles had a nice long lunch.  Once that broke up, I headed to this cache on the way to the airport... the buffalo airport.  Thank goodness for unlimited miles on the rental agreement!

Awesome cache, awesome location.... I did get a bit muddy on the way out as I wasn't paying as much attention after claiming the oldest/active in another state!

thanks for keeping this one going so long!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="31.23875" lon="-92.622117"><time>2001-04-21T00:00:00</time><name>GC763</name><desc>Wild Azalea Cache by TJ Willy</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC763</url><urlname>Wild Azalea Cache</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="1891" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Wild Azalea Cache</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>TJ Willy</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="1820">TJ Willy</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="1" inc="1">Dogs</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="32" inc="1">Bicycles</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="56" inc="1">Medium hike (1 km–10 km)</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="40" inc="1">Stealth required</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="38" inc="1">Campfires</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="18" inc="1">Dangerous animals</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="19" inc="1">Ticks</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="17" inc="1">Poisonous plants</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="39" inc="1">Thorns</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="22" inc="1">Hunting area</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>3.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>3</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Louisiana</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;LOUISIANA'S OLDEST ACTIVE GEOCACHE&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Wild Azalea trail has moderate changes in elevations at times. Also under wet conditions - creeks may overflow causing ankle deep water over parts of the trail. Forest service maintained and kept in great shape.&lt;/p&gt;

</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>A creek surrounds this primitive camping area. Cacher will need to cross devise a way to avoid the local hazard to get to the cache. There is considerable foliage, but I was able to get at least 3 satellite locks at all times. The container is a newly refurbished Ammo Can. Please be sure and take great care in camouflaging the container when you replace it and watch for muggles. The little secluding camping spot is growing in popularity from when I found it years ago... this according to what I have heard. Thanks.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;p&gt;UPDATE: 03.18.2004 - Please be sure to rehide this cache very well once you locate it. This "camping spot" is getting more and more popular and now that Spring is upon us - the tents will come back out. Just be sure it is covered completely before leaving. THANKS!!!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;UPDATE: 10.18.2009 - It has come to my attention that the can needs replacing. I am unable to get to that location right now and would like to work with another cacher to get that replaced. Please contact me through geocaching.com and we can work something out. I will update this listing again with a thank you note to the cacher that helps me keep this cache as nice as the location it is hidden. Thanks :)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;UPDATE: 5/13/2010 - Broken Trowel contacted me before heading to WA cache stating he would do his best to replace the container. Once he got there, a control burn had all but destroyed the old cache. Lots of logs were lossed dating back many years now. BT called me asking for guidance in replacing the cache as he went to special trouble and effort (not being local to the area) to put a new cache together. We devised with my goals for the cache in mind and his onsite reconnaissance a new location that suits the cache well.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;THANK YOU Broken Trowel for stepping up and helping to preserve this cache. It means so much to me. And I think a few other people in Louisiana. All my best, Phil.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;THANK YOU to Bonsaai for refurbishing this historic cache!&lt;/p&gt;

</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints /><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1364110115"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-28T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="205965">Moose Mob</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Road trip with me &amp; Bucky. This was my 50th state visited and geocached in and another state oldest to boot!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363907793"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-25T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="48318008">dobiest</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Found while traveling through after GeoWoodstock XXII. It was a nice hike out. Some previous logs made it really seem like this was going to be a chore, but Troopbiz and I made some quick work of it. Really enjoyed it! TFTC SL</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363885813"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-25T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2464712">Troopbiz</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">**Wild Azalea Cache**
**Find #22820**
**State Oldest #37**

**About This Cache**
In preparation for this cache, I did a lot of research regarding the best way to approach it. Luckily, some helpful logs made this a quick and easy adventure.

PARKING: N 31° 14.277 W 092° 37.660
TRAIL HEAD: N 31° 14.313 W 092° 37.645
LEAVE TRAIL: N 31° 14.353 W 092° 37.357

This was a beautiful 20-minute walk through the pine forest, but absolutely brutal in the post-storm humidity. Made quick work of locating the cache and replaced as found. Thanks for keeping this oldie alive!

**About My Trip**
Exploring Hot Springs today with DOBIEST before heading south to find Louisiana’s oldest, high point, and Cache Across America. Enjoying the bayou! All logs are signed “TB” or “Troopbiz”. Thanks, TJ Willy, for placing and maintaining this cache! TFTC SL</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1362336976"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-20T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="981641">zoothornrollo</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Quite the adventure! More later, when I get to a computer.  
I made it to a computer, so here goes…. we have found a cache in every county (parish) in the lower 48 states, so we are working on new icons in each state.  Mrs. Z isn’t up to long hikes any more, so my 71-year-old self set out solo.  The trail wasn’t as well marked as I hoped, and I ended up on s 2 track service road.  After a bushwhack back to the actual trail, I managed to sign the log, although I went around in circles getting to the cache.  This made the oldest cache in 23 states, and today I got Octapus Garden!  We also have Canada’s First!   I dragged myself back to the geo-mobile -barely- and off we went for more (hopefully less strenuous) attempts.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1362114120"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-19T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="5141535">sirkdizzzle</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Didn't plan it this way, but this is number 22,000 for me. This is a pretty memorable one, because as I was signing the log I heard a rustle behind me and turned around to see an armadillo family walking in my direction. I got some nice photos and a little video of them running past. Quite the hike out here, I'm glad I started at sunrise so at least the heat is manageable. Tad bit humid.

Spending the week on the road pursuing oldies, virtuals and other cool stops along the way from New Orleans to Kansas for Geowoodstock XXII weekend with the homies. 

Thanks to TJ Willy for placing this Traditional Cache for me to find!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="39.294533" lon="-76.7825"><time>2001-02-04T00:00:00</time><name>GC1FD</name><desc>Jusef's Cache by Scott &amp; Christine (maintained by MGS)</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC1FD</url><urlname>Jusef's Cache</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="509" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Jusef's Cache</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Scott &amp; Christine (maintained by MGS)</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="45039">mdgps</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="1" inc="1">Dogs</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="13" inc="0">Available 24/7</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="7" inc="1">Takes less than one hour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="53" inc="0">Park and grab</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="2" inc="1">Access/parking fee</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="32" inc="0">Bicycles</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="18" inc="1">Dangerous animals</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="19" inc="1">Ticks</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="17" inc="1">Poisonous plants</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>3</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>2</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Maryland</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>Jusef's Cache is located in the &lt;a href="http://www.dnr.state.md.us/publiclands/Pages/central/patapscohollofield.aspx"&gt;Hollofield area of Patapsco Valley State Park.&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
Please see the related web page for hours and fees to enter.
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;p&gt;This is officially the oldest active cache in the state of Maryland. You are discouraged from leaving trackables in this cache. Trackable visits encouraged! Please honor park hours and &lt;b&gt;take the white blazed trail from parking down the hill till near the cache&lt;/b&gt;. Trailhead coordinates available.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The cache was originally located under an old steel wash tub on a hill overlooking the Patapsco River and the Baltimore and Ohio Railroad.&lt;/p&gt;
The steel washtub has disintegrated over the years but the cache is very close to the original location.
&lt;p&gt;The original details:&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;i&gt;The container is a small Folgers coffee can. The original contents consist of a magnetic backgammon game and a digital wrist watch.&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;center&gt;This cache has been adopted by:
&lt;table border="1" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" bordercolor="#111111" width="50%"&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td width="100%" bgcolor="#FFFFFF" align="center"&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.mdgps.org" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;img src="http://www.mdgps.org/mdgpsbanner.gif" border="0" width="468" height="60" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/center&gt;

</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Current hint:  Its in the rocks.
Original hint:  On top of rock face. PLEASE USE THE TRAIL.</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1363541967"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-25T13:03:03</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="43047660">rydem3</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Final 15 feet are a bit tricky. Tftc!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363540554"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-25T12:58:31</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="8310104">zaccari</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">This has been on my radar for a while.   Glad to have it in hand.  Removed the TB so it doesn't get lost.   All is good here.   TFTC SL </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1362854689"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-23T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2508723">fondue4two</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">We paid five dollars per person to enter the park, and got our park map. We parked near the trailhead, and we were the only vehicle in the entire parking lot. Why? Maybe because it’s pouring rain. Thankfully we brought hiking sticks along as we are navigating up and down a slick muddy trail. Arrived at ground zero and made the find. So far the only blood drawn was in the parking lot when one of us whacked her hand on the car. It’s 09:33 in the morning, it’s still pouring rain. We’ve signed the log and dropped trackables. Please do not keep these trackables, but move them along. One of them is in a race for miles
Greetings from Madison Wisconsin thank you for keeping this old alive. This is another State oldie for us #33!!! 🥳🥳🥳🥳🥳❤️🫕</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363232276"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-14T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="31120311">Dyonstage</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Out &amp; about w/Smile612.  That was quite the hike - but most of the old ones are!  We made it a little too difficult for ourselves in an attempt to find a "shortcut," but should have stayed the course.  After reaching GZ, I made a few attempts to find it - and find it I did!  Thanks for keeping this alive!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1362738791"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-14T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="5602972">smile612</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Found it with Dyonstage 😁 On a long weekend road trip to get MD and VAs oldest geocaches to add to the collection and get some new Jasmer spots as well.  This one took a while as somehow we went the long way to get it.  We needed to consult some prior logs and pictures to narrow down the hiding spot for it.  Dyonstage made the track down the slope and after a while made the find!  I found a less steep way down to get to the cache.

The cache and log were in good shape.  We signed the log and took some pictures and returned the cache as found. FAV point given!💚 

Thanks to Scott&amp;Christine for creating the cache mdgps for keeping this oldie going through adoption, the adventure, and smile!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="42.62355" lon="-91.566367"><time>2001-01-13T00:00:00</time><name>GC162</name><desc>Maltese Goldfinch (Re-resurrected) by Wulfgar</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC162</url><urlname>Maltese Goldfinch (Re-resurrected)</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="354" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Maltese Goldfinch (Re-resurrected)</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Wulfgar</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="1697">wulfgar</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes /><groundspeak:difficulty>3</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>3.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Iowa</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>Backbone State Park
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>The Maltese Goldfinch is back. Iowa's longest-running geocache was reestablished Jan. 20, 2002, and is in operation once again. The original contents include: "Secret of the Yamas" book, mini water garden, sports card, Eternal Ink sticker, 3 skull rings, Isle of Capri key chain and, of course, a monk's bead. It is in an ammo box. There is a good uphill hike involved but no technical climbing needed. The park and area of the cache have great topography -- for Iowa. Standard Iowa disclaimers apply. It's buggy and weedy in the warm months, muddy in the wet months, frostbitten in the cold months. During winter, automobile access to the park is limited, so prepare for a longer walk.
</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>encased in stone near your feet</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1364268277"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-29T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="5604411">Obilon</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Well, sadly, I spent all of my allotted time looking for the 1/2 mi. trail, w/o success.
I got Within a quarter mile of it on the road, but could see that there was no Trail in bushwacking would be not only verbotten, but even possibly downright dangerous.
I drove down to the dry creek and found a grassy area. Exploring it I found a deer trail that looked to be about what geocachers would leave, but following it for about a hundred yards ended back at the river. I saw no sign of it otherwise. The only other option would have been to go to the main trailhead, but I had run out of time. Don't know when I'll ever be back. Really disappointed not to be able to grab this one.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364390530"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-28T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="382938">incepit</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">A nice walk, a bit of a hill at the end, but I was expecting much worse reading others logs.  Spotted a lot of deer on the short walk.  Found on our finding oldest caches road trip.  Thanks for the fun and the cache.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363965848"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-27T22:45:26</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="22628262">marla45</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">9926 current count

Out from Yuma Arizona with a few likeminded friends for GWXXII and ahem, a few other targets.  GC162   Maltese Goldfinch (Re-resurrected)
was one of them:

Final cache of the day, ending on a high note! Thanks for taking care of this oldie!

If answers were required one of us four sent them for all of us.

Nice cache-thanks for placing it here for us to find. Alls well here unless otherwise noted.

Running amok thru 5 states gathering states oldest, counties, challenges and anything else that comes our way. RoxieMama, KoolWaters, Earthikers and of course ParkerSaru are on a journey for both smiles and laughs.Stopping for caches, interesting places and more.

Thanks, wulfgar for the fun! 
May 27, 2026
</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363967590"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-27T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="5135545">smitranm</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">[:)] Day thirteen of two week road trip GeoWoodstock XXII in Kansas as the main goal. Moline, IL to Sioux Falls, SD. Morning clouds soon disappeared, sunny and hot. Eighteen finds and a DNF. Thank you for the cache. A favorite.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363965849"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-27T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="5135553">smitranp</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">[:)] Long but satisfying day. Found Iowa's oldest, finished last portion of a county chain from Atlantic to Pacific, one of two webcams, highest location in Iowa, and an excellent letterbox. Thank you for the cache.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="42.460433" lon="-71.157033"><time>2000-10-01T00:00:00</time><name>GC74</name><desc>First Mass by Jeremy Gilbert - adopted by g-o-cashers</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC74</url><urlname>First Mass</urlname><sym>Geocache Found</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="116" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>First Mass</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Jeremy Gilbert - adopted by g-o-cashers</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="123197">g-o-cashers</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes /><groundspeak:difficulty>1.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>2</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Massachusetts</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>I have set up what I think is the first GPS Cache / Stash in MA state. It is a "suburban cache", easy to reach from anywhere in the greater Boston area. The location easy to get to on foot but slightly off the beaten path. There is some treasure that will be amusing to Boston-area residents. Also, head 100 meters South and 100 meters North for some great area views!
&lt;p&gt;254 ft elevation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Good hunting!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Note from g-o-cashers: &lt;b&gt;Containers I place at the original location continue to go missing. I'll try to maintain a secondary container within 25' of the original coordinates. Subtract .004 from the west coordinates to locate this medium sized lock-n-lock container. Signing either container counts as a find, signing both still counts as one find! Please don't leave Travel Bugs in this cache.&lt;/b&gt; Many non-cachers visit the container, sign the log and in some cases take travel bugs. I'm going to leave the cache this way because I think it is important to preserve the original location, but it is not safe to leave bugs here.&lt;/p&gt;

</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints /><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1364743518"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-31T18:33:16</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="55406433">LazarA16</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Tftc</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364743405"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-31T18:32:42</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="43963933">Dan475</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">tftc</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364168410"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-29T09:03:26</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="11454452">P_E_M</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Very cool that this cache is still active. Thank you for maintaining it.

Could use a new logbook and some pens 😃

Gets a fav for sure</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364166679"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-29T08:53:18</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="44461750">ladyfish96</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">With pem TFTC</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363890012"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-26T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1491213">softball29</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Off on a wild day of adventure with JK186 to the Boston area for some caches, the Stamp Expo, lobstah rolls and good weather! Sometimes the mind and body need a day away to be in a good place. It's always nice to get the oldest in a state. Once we found prking, we were on our way. Not a long way, but up. Once in the area, it didn't take too long to find. Dropped a couple of flashtags. Earns a favorite point for sure. Log book is nearly full... could use a new one! Signed and replaced. Thanks for the smiley! 

HooHaa Blog: [My blog about caching and more](http://www.hoohaablog.com/)</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="703112234"><groundspeak:date>2017-07-19T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2089726">travelingGeek</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Wow, another oldest in the state and another for my collection of 4 character GC codes! 

Cache and log in good condition but the zip lock doesn't close.  Seems ok as the container is waterproof for now. 

I'm from clay Texas so the T2 surprised me.  I may have taken an unorthodox approval to gz but had fun doing it. 

Thanks for keeping this one going.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="44.86951666666667" lon="-85.58045"><time>2000-07-16T00:00:00</time><name>GC35</name><desc>Power Island by Kluso</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC35</url><urlname>Power Island</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="53" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Power Island</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Kluso</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="22">kluso</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Other</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes /><groundspeak:difficulty>3.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Michigan</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description /><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;P&gt;
Stash container is a red cylinder approximately 10.5” x 6”.
&lt;P&gt;
Stash is located on Power Island. Once owned by the Henry Ford family, this
island is now a nature preserve. 
&lt;P&gt;&lt;B&gt;A few rustic camping sites are available
on nearby Bassett Island, which is connected to Power Island by an isthmus.
Camping reservations may be needed.&lt;/B&gt;
&lt;P&gt;
The location description below was found 
&lt;A HREF="http://www.insiders.com/traverse/main-parks3.htm"&gt;here&lt;/A&gt;..
&lt;P&gt;
Power Island
Bowers Harbor, West Grand Traverse Bay, Traverse City • (231) 922-4818
Formerly known as Marion Island but recently renamed for philanthropist
Eugene Power of Ann Arbor, this is a 205-acre island nature preserve in West
Grand Traverse Bay just off Bower's Harbor. This island is one of the last
undeveloped Great Lakes islands in close proximity to an urban area. It is
filled with a beautiful stand of northern hardwoods, including beech, sugar
maple, basswood and red oak, as well as more than 250 plant species.
Wildlife includes red fox and bobcat who prey on such small mammals as the
meadow vole, woodland deer mouse and short-tailed shrew. Bird-watchers will
likely see the red-eyed vireo, American goldfinch, veery and bank and tree
swallow. Approximately 11 miles of hiking trails weave through the island's
interior. Due to Power Island's proximity to Traverse City, it is a popular
boating and picnicking destination. </groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Located beneath a rock beneath a big tree. </groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1364213829"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-29T13:35:44</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="802439">itscherij</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">I still have 2 spots remaining with Captain Mike for Saturday, June 6 at 9 am. PM me if you’re interested. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364242692"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-29T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="287644">abnduo&amp;spawn</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">We came to Michigan to visit family for Memorial Day weekend, once the family gathering was done we decided it was a great opportunity to have a little vacation and grab some caches in the counties we did not have any finds and light them up on our Michigan counties map for the state challenge, along with grabbing some of the legacy (grandfather, if you will) caches for the Jasmer challenges. We have been wanting to get back up here to abn2's home state, and do this type of trip for a while. This was the perfect opportunity.

As so many others have done, we made the trek here specifically to get this legacy cache for our Jasmer matrix. We knew we were going to be making a trip to Michigan for our family reunion as mentioned above, and called to make arrangements with CPT Mike to get us to the island. We had seen a note on the cache page of others looking to get there this week, so we arranged it on a day that rebekah13 could join us. abn1 and abn2 had been to the island many years ago, almost 27 years to be exact, so long before Geocaching was even created, so we knew we had to make this trek and get this specific cache for our Jasmer. CPT Mike got us safely to the island, and even helped us with an attack plan to ensure we had ample time to get all but one of the caches on the island. All in all a great day. As a bonus this was our first find in Grand Traverse County. TFTC!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364208581"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-29T10:31:19</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="13680496">rebekah13</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Joined captain Mike and the abnduo&amp;spawn couple! I even got my muggle husband to come!
Such a beautiful area and beautiful scenery. Easily my favorite oldest I’ve found scenery wise!

Back in 2024, I decided to create a wild goal. I want to find the oldest in every state. I’ve made great improvements! This is my 11th! Here’s my list so far:

2024:
Tennessee
Alabama
Georgia

2025:
Missouri
Nebraska
Colorado
Kansas
Wisconsin 

2026:
Illinois
Iowa
Michigan

Tomorrow, I’ll be adding Indiana and in a couple months, I’ll also get Minnesota! So glad to be accomplishing my goal little by little!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364105446"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-28T19:17:52</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1025827">Taylor.Ann</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Hello! Heading to Power Island on June 7 with captain Mike at 900am. If anyone would like to join and split costs please private message me. There is space for 4 more </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363798921"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-26T18:37:16</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="3855841">Macro and 2 Micros</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Bucket list!   Couldn’t resist stepping off to the beach!   Thanks for keeping this going!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="47.985033" lon="-92.8272"><time>2000-11-05T00:00:00</time><name>GC9FF</name><desc>Alvin's Phone Line by Ken Walker</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC9FF</url><urlname>Alvin's Phone Line</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="2559" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Alvin's Phone Line</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Ken Walker</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="5947">kwalker</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Large</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="1">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="13" inc="0">Available 24/7</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="56" inc="1">Medium hike (1 km–10 km)</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="14" inc="0">Recommended at night</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="44" inc="1">Flashlight required</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="30" inc="1">Picnic tables nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="34" inc="0">Quads</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="35" inc="0">Off-road vehicles</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="15" inc="1">Available in winter</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="36" inc="0">Snowmobiles</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="49" inc="1">May require snowshoes</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="18" inc="1">Dangerous animals</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="19" inc="1">Ticks</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="22" inc="1">Hunting area</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>3</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Minnesota</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>&lt;p class="MsoNormal"&gt;Be sure to mark a waypoint before you walk into the woods here, it is easy to get lost! Also, it can be a fairly rough hike, depending on the season.&lt;/p&gt;

</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;p class="MsoNormal"&gt;In the &lt;span class="GramE"&gt;&lt;b style="mso-bidi-font-weight:normal;"&gt;Summer&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;, you’ll find some dense foliage;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal"&gt;&lt;b style="mso-bidi-font-weight:normal;"&gt;Spring&lt;/b&gt;, mud and muck;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal"&gt;&lt;b style="mso-bidi-font-weight:normal;"&gt;Fall&lt;/b&gt;, rutting bucks and hunters with guns (please avoid this cache in November);&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal"&gt;&lt;span class="GramE"&gt;&lt;b style="mso-bidi-font-weight:normal;"&gt;Winter&lt;/b&gt;, deep snow and cold.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal"&gt;This is the &lt;b style="mso-bidi-font-weight:normal;"&gt;&lt;span style="color:green;"&gt;first cache stashed in the state of MN!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt; You'll have to trek through a good bit of woods (public land) and down an old deer trail (private land). The land owners (&lt;span class="GramE"&gt;myself&lt;/span&gt; included) are all aware that cache seekers will be afoot and there's no problem whatsoever... &lt;b style="mso-bidi-font-weight:normal;"&gt;as long as you don't go through there during deer season (month of November). Please be respectful of this as there are many hunters in the area.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal"&gt;&lt;b style="mso-bidi-font-weight:normal;"&gt;Despite many pleas, warning, and signs posted in the area, three cachers recently stomped through the grounds in the middle of November!  If this happens again, we will have to close it down!  PLEASE DO NOT seek this cache in November!&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal"&gt;Please log your name in the book and treasure the contents of the stash! There is a complete explanation of why we called this "Alvin's Phone Line" contained in the cache. &lt;span class="GramE"&gt;Its&lt;/span&gt; a nice story and the trip in to find the cache is well worth your time.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal"&gt;&lt;b style="mso-bidi-font-weight:normal;"&gt;UPDATE&lt;/b&gt;: Unless a frightened Hippie has disposed of it to "save the earth," there should be one of Alvin's last bullets in the cache. Out of respect for Alvin (and not for the Hippie), we ask that you leave it there. It is certainly not dangerous, it will not spontaneously "blow up" (unless it gets up to 500 degrees next summer) and it won't hurt anyone unless they decide to bang on it with a hammer (please don't do this).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal"&gt;&lt;b style="mso-bidi-font-weight:normal;"&gt;UPDATE&lt;/b&gt;: I can't stress this enough, please DO NOT attempt to find this cache in November. It is hunting season. There are lots of hunters in that area with very powerful guns, and stomping around in the woods without any blaze orange clothing on is a great way to be mistaken for a deer. Besides, we, (the land/cache owners) are usually up there hunting in November and we don't wish to spook the woods any more than we have to. We respectfully ask that you save your enthusiasm for December or anytime prior to November!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal"&gt;&lt;b style="mso-bidi-font-weight:normal;"&gt;UPDATE&lt;/b&gt;: It came to our attention on 5/20/2012 that someone took the explanation/story out of the cache, and apparently took it home with them. *sigh* Do I really need to mention that the story should stay WITH the cache so that other visitors can learn of the significance of the location? If you've logged a visit here, please email me (the cache owner) and I'll be happy to pass along the story. It has since been replaced. Please; leave the story (and Alvin's picture) at the cache site, in their zip-top bags! Also, it would appear that Alvin's bullet is missing. Again. We may not have another one, I'll need to check Alvin's old stash box at the cabin. Please don't take the bullet, if you have an issue with it or you would like to express your concern, please contact the owner of the cache. Thanks!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal"&gt;&lt;b style="mso-bidi-font-weight:normal;"&gt;UPDATE&lt;/b&gt;: We have strung a cable across the general "yard" area to keep out "casually curious" trespassers. There is plenty of room to park on just outside of the cable and, as usual, if you're a geo-cacher, feel free to hop over the cable and hunt away!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal"&gt;&lt;b style="mso-bidi-font-weight:normal;"&gt;UPDATE&lt;/b&gt;: Alvin's chair (you'll know it when you see it) has become very brittle, after spending many decades outside in the weather. As tempting as it might be to have a seat and take a selfie, PLEASE, in the interest of historical preservation, do NOT sit in the chair! You don't want to be the one to break it!!&lt;/p&gt;
One last thing, BE CAREFUL and watch your footing! If you trip and fall or poke yourself in the eye with a stick, you are liable for your own injuries!
</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints /><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1364257620"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-29T15:34:49</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="24603519">Jittney</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">We finally crossed this one off our bucket list!  With it being our home state, one could assume we'd have found it already.  Not the case.  I guess being our home state there was no urgency.  It is our 11th find of a state's oldest active cache.
We are in the area for our extended family's annual Summer Christmas.  Despite coming here every summer for years, we never noticed just how close to Alvin we were.  Once we noticed, we had no excuse not to go for the find.  (Close = 71 minutes.  Once we've gone this far, what's an extra 71 minutes?)
This appears to be a great time of year to go for this one.  The trail was relatively dry, there were no mosquitoes, the temperature was warm.  I can't imagine better conditions for this trail.
We grabbed a couple TBs to move along, left nothing but our signature, and replaced it as found.  TFTC!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364391282"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-29T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="382938">incepit</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Our last oldest cache find on our roadtrip. I did end up picking up a few ticks here.  Thanks for the story and the cache.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364201609"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-29T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="928650">caviar42</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">After Geowoodstock, this was next on our to do list. We were prepared for mosquitoes, there were none. It was a bit mucky, but no issues. Used previous cachers coords for parking. Just a short. .15 walk. Found in great shape. Took a TB and left a few. Many thanks to the owner for maintaining this oldest cache. Greetings from Florida. Giving this one a fav point. TFTF.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1362384237"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-20T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="47911">medicineman</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">On a road trip to geocaching HQ and targeting the oldest in each state we go through. This started us off in fine style. Cache is in great shape. Signed the log and traded pathtags. A little tricky finding the way in. Parked at N47 59.092 W92 49.815.  Found trailhead at N47 59.103 W92 49.806. From there it was easy though a bit soggy right now. Many thanks and a favorite, of course.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363314947"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-18T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="30156214">Cache_keteer</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">More larer</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="32.3523333333333" lon="-88.6671666666667"><time>2000-10-19T00:00:00</time><name>GC90</name><desc>Bonita Lakes by Tony Boutwell</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC90</url><urlname>Bonita Lakes</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="144" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Bonita Lakes</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Tony Boutwell</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="335">GeoTony</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Not chosen</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="42" inc="1">Needs maintenance</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>2</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>2</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Mississippi</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>First Geocache for Mississippi. This is located on the outskirts of
the town of Meridian. The jumping off point is the beautiful Bonita
Lakes. There are many hiking/biking routes through out this area.
Tree coverage will be an ISSUE if you are using an older GPS. A
friend of mine joined me with a very nice high-end Sony GPS system
(4-5 years old) and his system had trouble keeping satellite locks.
I used the new Garmin eMap which seemed to work through the trees
with no problem. Total elevation climb will be around 550 ft. An
uprooted tree and the color blue will mark the spot.
</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1364460787"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-30T15:51:21</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1274611">AngelBandit</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Came over from PCB to get this cache. It leaves us only one JASMER spot to fill and we will get it next month on our Cache Cruise. Thank you so much for maintaining this oldie so those of us newer to the game have these opportunities. Fave point. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363957265"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-27T19:16:28</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="95396">Me &amp; Bucky</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Bucky &amp; I found this one with Moose Mob on an amazing day of caching. The temp was in the mid 80s in a cloudy, hazy, muggy sky with occasional rain. 

This is Day 17 on our trip to GeoWoodstock XXII!   Stayed in Jonesboro, Arkansas last night and now we’re headed south and east into Mississippi.  

Third time here for this one.  First found it in 2013, then 3 years ago in 2023 while cruising around with Moun10Bike.  Now back again, visiting it with Moose Mob. 

Thanks for the fun!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363959882"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-27T18:59:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="205965">Moose Mob</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Proud member of the coordinate verification and pencil distribution team.

Roadtrip from Jonesboro to Meridian with me &amp; Bucky, finding a few geocaches along the way.  

Watering coronavirus bushes and irritating the ticks!

[Nevada Geocaching](http://www.facebook.com/groups/337489309623791/)
[Geocachers of Mesquite Nevada](https://www.facebook.com/groups/333103173116062)
[Southern Utah Geocachers](https://www.facebook.com/groups/144535995603653)
[Geocaching Korea](https://www.facebook.com/groups/geocachekorea)
[Northern Arizona Geocachers](https://www.facebook.com/groups/NAZGeocachers)
[OVC - Ojai Valley Cachers](http://www.facebook.com/groups/OjaiValleyCachers/)
[Poison Oak Cachers - San Luis Obispo and beyond](https://www.facebook.com/groups/poisonoakcachers)
[Bay Area Geocachers](https://www.facebook.com/groups/BayAreaGeocachers)
</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363225948"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-24T09:41:36</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="13143252">SoDakZak</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Quick find on a nice hike that broke up a 12+ hour road trip from Alabama to hot springs (with some detours for caches). I’m so happy to check another oldest off the map!! Favorite awarded for the history and hike! </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364833800"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-21T10:09:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="35451479">naturelvr59</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Bad timing with Mother Nature. Will attempt another day. 
  Sweetbeamie and I, along with our Geopup Little Bear are headed to GeoWoodstock 2026! Our second GeoWoodstock. 
 We spent May 17th to May 24th traveling from our home in Elkhart Indiana through OH, KY, TN, NC, SC, GA, FL, LA, MS, AR, MO, KS, NE, IA, IL. 
 So many goals checked off and so many cool caches along the way. Including GC30 MINGO. Thanks to every geocacher that puts out and maintains caches for us all to enjoy in our adventures across this great country.   TFTC</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="38.943933" lon="-94.60315"><time>2000-06-20T00:00:00</time><name>GC37</name><desc>Missouri's First - Watts Mill by Steve Brown (Adopted by OrigamiFolder)</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC37</url><urlname>Missouri's First - Watts Mill</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="55" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Missouri's First - Watts Mill</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Steve Brown (Adopted by OrigamiFolder)</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="2678106">OrigamiFolder</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="24" inc="1">Wheelchair accessible</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="1">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="8" inc="1">Scenic view</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="13" inc="1">Available 24/7</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="7" inc="1">Takes less than one hour</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="40" inc="1">Stealth required</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="37" inc="0">Horses</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="15" inc="1">Available in winter</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="17" inc="1">Poisonous plants</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>1</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Missouri</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>&lt;a href="https://s3.amazonaws.com/gs-geo-images/55efcb97-c661-4b04-9465-317a8c939380_l.jpg"&gt;&lt;img src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/gs-geo-images/55efcb97-c661-4b04-9465-317a8c939380_l.jpg" align="center" alt="Click to view the larger picture" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;font size="+1" color="blue"&gt;Missouri's First Geocache site.&lt;/font&gt;
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;p&gt;The following is Steve's original listing:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;Today at lunch(6-20-2000), I read about GPS Stash Hunting on the sci.geo.satellite-nav USENET newsgroup and found Mike Teague's home page. Check it out and then click on Missouri listed under "Active Stashes". &lt;a href="http://web.archive.org/web/20000621194709/http://www.triax.com/yngwie/gps.html"&gt;http://www.triax.com/yngwie/gps.html&lt;/a&gt; I could not find any Geocache sites to go hunt this evening so I went out in the rain and made my own. I expect it to be the first in Kansas City(turns out to be the first in Missouri). I found a nice location along side the Watts Mill walking/bicycle trail in South Kansas City.
&lt;p&gt;As of March 2002 the trail is now completed from a little east of here, to about 35 miles in the south end of Olathe, KS. I have walked the entire trail. It's paved all the way. It's great for walking, jogging, biking or roller blading.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The shortest distance from the trail is not the best route. Please check for muggles along the creek before you go after the cache. The muggles have stolen the cache twice so far. &lt;strong&gt;Please rehide as well as you found it or better.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A wheelchair can get fairly close.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt;8/25/2022 Note:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;One faithful day in June of 2000 Steve Brown read an article about "GPS Stash Hunting" on an old USENET newsgroup website.  Fascinated by the idea but not seeing any local for him to find he went out in the rain that evening and hid a container along the &lt;a href="https://coord.info/GC37"&gt;Watts Mill&lt;/a&gt; trail.  In his log from that day he mentions that it is not only the first in Kansas City but the first in the state of Missouri adding "there was no caches closer than 350 miles to go hunt".  That other cache ~350 miles away was none other than &lt;a href="https://coord.info/GC30"&gt;Mingo&lt;/a&gt;, the oldest active cache in the world!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GC37"&gt;GC37&lt;/a&gt; sat unfound for more than 3 months until it was &lt;a href="https://coord.info/GLAE8"&gt;finally discovered&lt;/a&gt;.  There were 25 unique finds that first year including one from none other than &lt;a href="https://coord.info/GL35FF"&gt;*gln&lt;/a&gt; the long time Missouri reviewer.  Since then it has been visited nearly 4,000 times by cachers from 27 different countries racking up more than 1,000 favorite points and helping to finish countless Jasmer grids.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In 2007 &lt;a href="https://www.geocaching.com/profile/?guid=dd08392e-ee4a-4e19-be70-48782bbd93d6"&gt;Steve Brown&lt;/a&gt; handed over ownership of the cache to Jim Shilt aka &lt;a href="https://www.geocaching.com/profile/?guid=0ab1a9e7-3ce7-4d27-bd71-850d452f0597"&gt;webscouter&lt;/a&gt;.  Jim was the caretaker until 2017 when he passed the rains to me (&lt;a href="https://www.geocaching.com/profile/?guid=f891042f-7771-4e79-a59f-745281b65c82"&gt;OrigamiFolder&lt;/a&gt;).  Like Steve and Jim before me I've found it a great honor to be the caretaker of this significant cache.  All 3 of us have had to replace the container and adjust the location to avoid muggles but we continue to do so to keep this beacon of geocaching alive for future visitors.  Scrolling through the old logs I see the names of many geocaching friends often mentioning it was among their first finds.  &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is currently the 14th oldest active geocache out of the more than 3 million worldwide. Please ensure that following your visit you have hid it in such a way to keep it alive for future generations. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;On this day I am officially moving it to avoid a housless camp and trail maintenance that has closed the original GZ area. Permission for this new location has been secured with Andrew Fleming the Area Superintendent (South District) for the Parks and Recreation Department of the City of Kansas City.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Thanks,&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;OrigamiFolder (Dave)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://info.flagcounter.com/ZklG"&gt;&lt;img alt="Flag Counter" src="https://s11.flagcounter.com/countxl_US/ZklG/bg_FFFFFF/txt_000000/border_CCCCCC/columns_8/maxflags_51/viewers_0/labels_1/pageviews_1/flags_0/percent_0/" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href="http://info.flagcounter.com/JdZu"&gt;&lt;img alt="Flag Counter" src="http://s10.flagcounter.com/map/JdZu/size_l/txt_000000/border_CCCCCC/pageviews_1/viewers_Cacher+Countries+Since+April+2017/flags_0/" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>This one is now a green tube on some downed logs. There are a few leaves on top of the container to hide it from the muggles.</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1364492333"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-30T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="53330126">BuzzBuzz969</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">I'm  in from Arizona for a couple days of caching before working with a client in the area. Previous logs and pictures helped me find this one. I'm excited to get this "oldest". TFTC</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364215174"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-29T12:45:30</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="8847997">after8</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">A hundred caches seem to have exploded on GZ. Luckily the proper one was intact. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364228005"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-29T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="1271259">NitiFlex</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Vacanze USA 2026 !!!
Come ogni anno eccomi nuovamente in partenza per il mio paese preferito.
Quest'anno ho una compagna di viaggio di livello "stratosferico", l'unica che abbia valutato la mia proposta interessante "after8". Sono ormai 3 anni abbondanti che inseguo le vecchie cache, voglio collezionare Jasmer. Purtroppo per problemi familiari non ho potuto supportare Laura le ultime 3 settimane e il viaggio ha rischiato di saltare ...
Un importante capitolo della mia vita si è concluso ma ora è il momento di cercare un pò di relax.
Percorreremo gli USA da est a ovest, da Atlanta a Phoenix, poche cache salvate nella lista ma di un livello importante.
Giorno 1:
Finisco di lavorare verso le 14.30 e in un'oretta mi ritrovo già in auto sull'e45 alla volta di Roma. Laura è al lavoro fino a tardi ma arriviamo quasi insieme a casa sua. Ottima cenetta e poi una bella passeggiata alla ricerca di una gelateria con cache lungo il tragitto.
Giorno 2 :
Ben poco da dire su questa giornata dedicata al viaggio, termina cmq poco prima di mezzanotte ma con tutto pronto per l'indomani....
Facciamo una Virtual in aeroporto per sentirci in vacanza.
Il meteo è pessimo in quanto diluvia con fulmini e tuoni ma soprattutto mette così per tutti i prossimi giorni...
Giorno 3 :
Alle 5.00 di mattina lasciamo la stanza e per colazione becchiamo una Waffle House che ci rifornisce di energie per la giornata di Geocaching. Non è bel tempo ma almeno non piove. Perdiamo 1 ora per un gennaio 2001 che non troviamo.... che delusione....
Per fortuna il resto della giornata fila liscio, anche troppo visto una mia caduta che mi ha tolto il fiato per 1 minuto, chissa domani come starò 😭.
Giorno 4 :
Secondo giorno di caccia alle oldy, oggi facciamo una puntatina in Alabama ma poi concluderemo la giornata ad Atlanta, sicuramente meno camminate ma molta più auto !!!
Giorno 5 :
Partenza sempre verso le 5.30, oggi la Coordinatrice di Viaggio after8 ha organizzato un bel viaggio in barca per Marooned. Ma prima di questo abbiamo l'unica cache che non potevo mancare e quella per la quale era obbligatorio venire in Georgia, l'ultimo agosto 2000 che mi mancava. Direi che sono il primo italiano a trovarle tutte e 4 !!!
Giorno 6 :
Stamattina in siamo partiti più tardi, tipo le 6.00 Hihihi.
Giornata con poche cache, ci dedichiamo alle "Welcome to" che servono a Laura e non faremo nessun 2000. Sosta per la spesa e tante miglia davanti.
Giorno 7 :
Stamattina ci svegliamo tardi ma abbiamo la colazione inclusa per cui non perdiamo tempo per il primo pasto della giornata. Tantissime miglia da macinare in auto, nel frattempo cerchiamo cose sfiziose da collezionare. Da oggi si va a cercare "pleasure" e "video game".
Giorno 8 :
Mattina da passare a Kansas City, non abbiamo tantissime cose in programma ma vicino a dove abbiamo dormito in tarda mattinata c'è un evento, per me che non ne faccio mai sarebbe una manna poterne loggare uno e aggiungere il tesoro relativo.
Nel tardo pomeriggio forse Mingo e Arikaree con puntatina in Nebraska che mi manca come stato.
Nanna nei paraggi...
About this cache :
All'arrivo nei paraggi di questa storica rimaniamo stupiti della situazione attorno alla cache. Non capiamo cosa può essere successo e non essendo del posto non prendiamo l'iniziativa di rimettere a posto il disordine di questi oggetti abbandonati.
La cache è presente e come per tutte queste vecchiette lascio un Punto Favorito. Spero che qualche giocatore del luogo dedichi un pò ti tempo per ristabilire l'ordine.
Thanks Owner</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364085445"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-28T15:00:09</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="28862402">LillianSeesing</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">tyy</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363960002"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-27T20:24:11</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="3423031">fam.vs.cache</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Always surprised how development of an area changes over 26 or so years.  Wonder what this area was like when this cache was placed.

All good with the cache.  Thanks for keeping this oldie going!
</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="45.92595" lon="-111.496883"><time>2001-03-14T00:00:00</time><name>GC493</name><desc>Missouri Headwaters by Don and Nancy Wilson</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC493</url><urlname>Missouri Headwaters</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="1171" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>Missouri Headwaters</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Don and Nancy Wilson</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="50069939">pospilgramage</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes /><groundspeak:difficulty>1</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>2</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Montana</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>Year round access. Some bushwhacking at the end.</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>Enjoy a visit to the headwaters of the Missouri River. Note there
is a 5$ fee for non-residents. Due North of the cache is a large
outcropping that Lewis and Clark climbed to view the Gallatin
Valley. Due West is a lookout to view the headwaters of the
Missouri River where the Jefferson and Madison rivers join. The
area can be very busy. The cache contains several camping type
implements and is found in a shoebox style rubber maid container.
Enjoy the visit to this historical place as you hunt this fun
cache. As of 4/27/07 the owners have signed up for a two year
Montana Fish Wildlife and parks permit to have this cache at this
site. I should also mention that there is a fee for out of state
visitors to this park.</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Beneath base of large downed cottonwood which points 128 M</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1364907448"><groundspeak:date>2026-06-01T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="47911">medicineman</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">On the way to Montana's oldest and had to score it's slightly younger brother. Took a hard way in and an easier way out. Signed the log. Thanks</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364081715"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-28T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="440566">Hounds In The Mist</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Great cache!  Took a few wrong turns until we found the correct geotrail. Beautiful area.  Happy to find this oldie!  Fav point! Signed log and swapped swag.   TFTC! 
On road trip from Washington state. </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363908000"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-27T11:36:27</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="3752706">eMichalek</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">My 📦 number 25410. 

My one month sabbatical has started on May 1st! We will spend with phylie the whole month in the US. After the East coast and Canada, we now continue to the West coast. 

Greetings from Minice in the Czech Republic 🇨🇿, proud member of European Union 🇪🇺

Thanks for the 📦 pospilgramage.

🇨🇿🇮🇹🇵🇱🇭🇷🇸🇮🇦🇹🇩🇪🇸🇰🇳🇱🇭🇺🇮🇸🇪🇸🇬🇮🇷🇴🇷🇸🇵🇹🇨🇭🇱🇮🇲🇨🇫🇷🇬🇧🇩🇰🇸🇪🇹🇷🇱🇻🇫🇮🇺🇸🇨🇦

Found with 📱 iP15Pro a app Cachly. 

ℹ️ In 2025 we will meet at:
👼🏻🎅👹 Mega event [Mikulášská nadílka / St. Nicholas´ Eve](https://coord.info/GCB2222) 5. 12. 2026 👼🏻🎅👹</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363907195"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-27T11:31:47</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="577767">phylie</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">We travel with eMichalek to USA 🇺🇸 and Canada 🇨🇦 and USA 🇺🇸 again (this time West coast - WA, OR and CA) for his one month long sabbatical (I am so jealous!) and we have decided to also take this as an opportunity to visit some local geocaching highlights. This 📦 from owner Don and Nancy Wilson could not be left behind during our looong hikes. Wish Missouri Headwaters long life. 🧡✌🏼🦎🇨🇿 TFTC, greetings from Minice, CZ, Europe.

We cordially invite all owners as well as geocachers to our next megaevent [St Nicholas’ Eve (for adults)](https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCB2222)</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363052928"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-18T10:05:12</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="39693733">cispecher</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Tftc samen met GH1964, TRIBBESNL, YIKVON uit Nederland gevonden. We zijn op een road trip van Las Vegas naar Seattle </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="40.914917" lon="-96.387583"><time>2001-05-10T00:00:00</time><name>GC943</name><desc>GO BIG RED by ABE &amp; RISS adopted by Nebraskache</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC943</url><urlname>GO BIG RED</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="2371" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>GO BIG RED</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>ABE &amp; RISS adopted by Nebraskache</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="157466">Nebraskache</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes /><groundspeak:difficulty>1.5</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>1.5</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Nebraska</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>We drove from Reno to the Midwest placing a cache in each state along our way.
&lt;p&gt;GO BIG RED is the Nebraska cache. Along with the log book and pencil we added local Reno/Tahoe goodies.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;bumper stickers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;post card&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;casino dice&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;deck of cards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;magnets, etc.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p style="margin-bottom:0in;text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;big&gt;&lt;big&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:bold;"&gt;October 28, 2012&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/big&gt;&lt;/big&gt;    &lt;big&gt;&lt;big&gt;&lt;span style="font-weight:bold;"&gt;Cache Update&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/big&gt;&lt;/big&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="margin-bottom:0in;"&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="margin-bottom:0in;"&gt;The old location for this cache has been changed due to road construction.  Thanks to catsnfish for moving their cache "Belmont Cemetery 1881" so there was room to place this cache in the area.  The  new location has safe parking away from the busy highway.  Please respect the area as you seek this cache.  You may park at or near these listed parking coordinates on Bluff Road. N40 54.861 W96 23.251 Thanks and good luck&lt;/p&gt;

</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints /><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1364886818"><groundspeak:date>2026-06-01T14:54:11</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="48173614">Mrcandybiker</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Amazing find thank you </groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364769045"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-31T15:43:53</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="8041283">thewildroseoftexas</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Delightful 

Log inked rcmp Today 

Here with Huggles44 

And Si McGnome of course

With Huggles44 at my side once more,
We launched our quest from county to county galore.
Armed with a GPS, snacks, and a plan half-baked,
We chased little containers wherever they were staked.

Like Lewis and Clark, we surveyed the land,
Though ours came with cache pages close at hand.
Across rolling fields and roads less traveled,
Our ambitious geo-scheme steadily unraveled.

A beaver appeared with a businesslike stare,
As if checking permits to see why we were there.
A snapping turtle lumbered along with great pride,
Suggesting our cache pace was a little slow by his side.

Wild turkeys gobbled opinions all day,
While pheasants exploded from ditches along the way.
Baby corn waved from fields neat as could be,
Though none seemed particularly interested in me.

EarthCaches called and we answered the test,
Studying geology with scholarly zest.
Measurements gathered and observations stored,
While Si McGnome photo-bombed every record.

At Virtuals he posed with his usual delight,
Appearing in pictures both left and right.
If there was a camera, a sign, or a view,
That gnome found a way to sneak into it too.

We scribbled our notes and signed when we could,
Finding hidden treasures exactly as geocachers should.
Each cache we discovered brought smiles anew,
Thanks to creative owners like all of you.

For without your effort, your hiding, your care,
There'd be far fewer adventures waiting out there.
No counties to chase, no stories to tell,
No containers tucked cleverly under a shell.

So here's our salute from Team RCMP's crew,
From Huggles44, Si McGnome, and me too.
May your coordinates stay steady and true,
And your wildlife encounters be less judgmental than ours were too!

**TFTC!** 🌽🦫🐢🦃📸🧭🗺️🧙‍♂️
</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364091776"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-28T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="4142826">Team Chili Fries</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Woo hoo was headed back to Omaha and realized would be close to oldest in state and had to add to our list. Great placement and thanks for keeping active</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364046298"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-28T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2821972">pamlicojack</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Staying in the area for a few days after GeoWoodstock and decided to come out here and grab this one. A nice bit of history and my 8th oldest find in a state.  TFTH...</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363913925"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-27T13:09:49</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="3423031">fam.vs.cache</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Another oldest state cache in the books.  Nice cemetery as a background.  Thanks for keeping this oldie going!
</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="38.409117" lon="-116.589367"><time>2000-12-26T00:00:00</time><name>GCF9</name><desc>XKD-380 by DS</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCF9</url><urlname>XKD-380</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="249" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>XKD-380</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>DS</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="847">DS</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Not chosen</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes /><groundspeak:difficulty>2</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>3</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>Nevada</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>Overall Difficulty: 2&lt;br&gt;
Terrain: Mostly 2 but maybe a 4 when you get close&lt;br&gt;
GPS receiver used: Garmin eTrex</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>This cache is in a remote area. The closest road is graded dirt and 
suitable for all vehicles.
&lt;p&gt;
Use common sense should you decide to look for this cache- particularly in 
the Summer months.  Carry plenty of water in your car and be sure to let 
someone know your plans including when you'll return home.
&lt;p&gt;
Hint: Once you've narrowed the search area take a minute and study the 
location from the road. Think about where you'd hide a cache- you'll 
probably come to the same decision I did.</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1364905603"><groundspeak:date>2026-06-01T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="26101408">Tw33k27</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Cache found, log signed, and cache replaced in good condition. 

Stopped to grab this one on my way back from Vegas and to get Nevada's oldies on the way home with the Mrs.  Yes it was a detour for it but while worth it.  I have attached a few photos of me near the GZ.   Favorite point awarded for this oldie.

It's not the destination that keeps me going. It's the journey and memories of all the fun caches I find along the way.  TFTC</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364500579"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-30T22:17:19</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2982809">brendabrnhrt</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">When Laurie told me we were super close to this old cache I knew we had to make the grab. So after parking the cache mobile we set off. It didn’t take long to find it but I may of had some help thanks to Laurie who already found it. But I inked the log and we headed on our way taking care of the ET Highway caches. Thank you so much for the great views!!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1360566509"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-12T06:57:30</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="609455">Data Wrangler</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Quite a trip to get out here and I was racing the sun. Had to search for a little while but persistence paid off. Glad to find this historical cache. Found while on a pre-GWXXII trip around the Southwest. SL, TFTC.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1358981894"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-02T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="8614773">Zargonians</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">We're staying in Tonopah for a couple of days specifically for getting Nevada's oldest geocache and caching a portion of the ET Highway on our way there.  We spent the better part of the morning and early afternoon caching the ET Highway on our way to this cache.  We parked off the road and made the short hike over to the cache, but had to backtrack a little when we realized we weren't close enough.  Once at the cache, we signed in the original logbook, dropped one off our trackable BamaRama 2026 caching cards, visited our trackables and took a few pictures.  Many thanks for keeping this oldie going!  Favorite point for sure!</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1355558468"><groundspeak:date>2026-04-16T16:04:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="30763633">BMFreeman</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Nevada a must find. (quaidsinthemmudd found it 8-28-2011 )oldest in Nevada 
So glad we took a short detour to find this one. Was cloudy and cool so made for a perfect day to do it. Thanks for keeping this oldie alive. We are heading to Arizona oldest next. Then on to Texas. A long drive from north Idaho. But always a good trip. We didn’t take the time to grab any of the power trail this trip gives us a reason to come back. ￼😜</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="42.753333" lon="-71.500083"><time>2000-10-29T00:00:00</time><name>GC9E</name><desc>NH #1 - Mines Follies by Paul Lamere, adopted by Nashuan,solid-rock-seekers</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GC9E</url><urlname>NH #1 - Mines Follies</urlname><sym>Geocache Found</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="158" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>NH #1 - Mines Follies</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>Paul Lamere, adopted by Nashuan,solid-rock-seekers</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="183909">solid-rock-seekers</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Regular</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:attribute id="6" inc="1">Recommended for kids</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="1" inc="1">Dogs</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="25" inc="1">Parking nearby</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="32" inc="1">Bicycles</groundspeak:attribute><groundspeak:attribute id="15" inc="1">Available in winter</groundspeak:attribute></groundspeak:attributes><groundspeak:difficulty>2</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>2</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>New Hampshire</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>
</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>&lt;p&gt;Come to our &lt;b&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GCAZVXN"&gt;Community Celebration Event&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/b&gt; to celebrate the 25th birthday of &lt;b&gt;&lt;a href="https://coord.info/GC9E"&gt;NH #1 - Mines Follies&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/b&gt; (this cache) and geocaching in New Hampshire!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Event:&lt;/b&gt; GCAZVXN Celebrating 25 Years of NH Geocaching at NH #1&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Date:&lt;/b&gt; Wednesday, October 29, 2025&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;Time:&lt;/b&gt; 4:00 p.m. to 6:00 p.m.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" align="center" style="text-align:center;margin:0in 0in 10pt;"&gt;&lt;b style="mso-bidi-font-weight:normal;"&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style="line-height:115%;font-size:20pt;"&gt;&lt;font face="Calibri"&gt;&lt;font size="6"&gt;History of Geocaching&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align:justify;margin:0in 0in 10pt;"&gt;&lt;font face="Calibri"&gt; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align:justify;margin:0in 0in 10pt;"&gt;&lt;font face="Calibri" size="4"&gt;Prior to May 2, 2000 GPS accuracy for publically available signals were intentionally limited to approximately&lt;/font&gt; &lt;a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Selective_Availability#Selective_availability"&gt;&lt;font color="#0000FF" face="Calibri" size="4"&gt;328 feet&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;font face="Calibri"&gt;&lt;font size="4"&gt;by including an amount or error in the signal by the U.S. government, hoping that this would deny an enemy the use of civilian GPS receivers for precision weapon guidance. With this amount of tolerance (bear in mind that +/- 328 feet is actually 656 feet in diameter) it would have not have been realistic for geocaching to come into being. At Midnight on May 1&lt;sup&gt;st&lt;/sup&gt;, the amount of error added was "set to zero” following an announcement by President Bill Clinton; and thus gave users access to the error-free L1 signal.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align:justify;margin:0in 0in 10pt;"&gt;&lt;font face="Calibri" size="4"&gt; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align:justify;margin:0in 0in 10pt;"&gt;&lt;font face="Calibri" size="4"&gt;On May 3&lt;sup&gt;rd&lt;/sup&gt; of that year computer consultant Dave Ulmer of Beaver Creek Oregon placed a 5-gallon black plastic bucket at the posted coords of N45°17.460 W122°24.800 and posted the&lt;/font&gt; &lt;a href="http://geocaching.gpsgames.org/history/announcement.txt"&gt;&lt;font color="#0000FF" face="Calibri" size="4"&gt;“Original Stash” to a usenet newsgroup&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;font face="Calibri" size="4"&gt;. By May 6, 2000, it had been found twice and logged once (by Mike Teague of Vancouver, Washington). A&lt;/font&gt; &lt;a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=LMHZcgM11GU&amp;amp;feature=youtube_gdata"&gt;&lt;font color="#0000FF" face="Calibri" size="4"&gt;video&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;font face="Calibri" size="4"&gt;survives that shows the original contents and log book. The initial term “stash” was deemed to carry with it certain negative connotations and on May 30&lt;sup&gt;th&lt;/sup&gt; the name “&lt;/font&gt;&lt;a href="http://groups.yahoo.com/group/gpsstash/message/62"&gt;&lt;font color="#0000FF" face="Calibri" size="4"&gt;geocache&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;font face="Calibri" size="4"&gt;” (being a combination of words: geo-earth, and cache – better word for stash) was substituted. By 8/16/2000 this was the list of&lt;/font&gt; &lt;a href="http://web.archive.org/web/20000817003939/http:/www.42nd-dimension.com/gps/caches.asp"&gt;&lt;font color="#0000FF" face="Calibri" size="4"&gt;available geocaches&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;font face="Calibri" size="4"&gt;– all 64 of them!&lt;/font&gt; &lt;a href="http://web.archive.org/web/20000621194709/http:/www.triax.com/yngwie/gps.html"&gt;&lt;font color="#0000FF" face="Calibri" size="4"&gt;this post&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;font face="Calibri"&gt;&lt;font size="4"&gt;by Dave Ulmer explained the basic principles of this new game and his insight to the possibilities was incredible.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align:justify;margin:0in 0in 10pt;"&gt;&lt;font face="Calibri" size="4"&gt; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align:justify;margin:0in 0in 10pt;"&gt;&lt;font face="Calibri" size="4"&gt;In September of 2000,&lt;/font&gt; &lt;a href="http://www.groundspeak.com/"&gt;&lt;font color="#0000FF" face="Calibri" size="4"&gt;Groundspeak.com&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;font face="Calibri" size="4"&gt;founder Jeremy Irish registered the domain name of&lt;/font&gt; &lt;a href="http://www.geocaching.com/"&gt;&lt;font color="#0000FF" face="Calibri" size="4"&gt;geocaching.com&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;font face="Calibri" size="4"&gt;and listed all available caches to this new geocaching site; incorporating new features to this rapidly growing sport, such as searching the site for nearby caches by zip code and the availability logging finds online. During highway maintenance, the&lt;/font&gt; &lt;a href="http://coord.info/GCF"&gt;&lt;font color="#0000FF" face="Calibri" size="4"&gt;original cache&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;font face="Calibri" size="4"&gt;site was accidentally destroyed by a road crew’s mower and the cache was feared lost. A team successfully located remnants of the historic cache and hit pay dirt when they found – the original can of beans. The lowly can of beans that Ulmer placed in the original five-gallon bucket had become the butt of geocaching jokes as a bit of swag that nobody wanted to trade for. A memorial plaque now sits at the actual site, and is findable as the Original Stash Tribute Plaque (&lt;/font&gt;&lt;a href="http://coord.info/GCGV0P"&gt;&lt;font color="#0000FF" face="Calibri" size="4"&gt;GCGV0P&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;font face="Calibri" size="4"&gt;). A cache page has since been established for the&lt;/font&gt; &lt;a href="http://coord.info/GCF"&gt;&lt;font color="#0000FF" face="Calibri" size="4"&gt;original stash&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;font face="Calibri"&gt;&lt;font size="4"&gt;, though it should be noted that because geocaching.com post-dated geocaching itself, that these early records are incomplete.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="margin:0in 0in 10pt;"&gt;&lt;font face="Calibri"&gt; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;font face="Calibri"&gt; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" align="center" style="text-align:center;margin:0in 0in 10pt;"&gt;&lt;b style="mso-bidi-font-weight:normal;"&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style="line-height:115%;font-size:20pt;"&gt;&lt;font face="Calibri"&gt;&lt;font size="6"&gt;Paul Lamere&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="margin:0in 0in 10pt;"&gt;&lt;font face="Calibri"&gt; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align:justify;margin:0in 0in 10pt;"&gt;&lt;font face="Calibri" size="4"&gt;In October of 2000, cacher&lt;/font&gt; &lt;a href="http://www.geocaching.com/profile/default.aspx?guid=6abe8879-19b3-49d2-ac91-eed581e171f6"&gt;&lt;font color="#0000FF" face="Calibri" size="4"&gt;Paul Lamere&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;font face="Calibri" size="4"&gt;was reading an&lt;/font&gt; &lt;a href="http://slashdot.org/story/00/09/25/2030252/geocaching"&gt;&lt;font color="#0000FF" face="Calibri" size="4"&gt;online article&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;font face="Calibri" size="4"&gt;about this new activity and his curiosity was piqued. Initially, he searched for nearby caches and after finding none locally, decided to place one himself. What he didn’t know at the time was that this would be New Hampshire’s first placed cache (and only the 158&lt;sup&gt;th&lt;/sup&gt; to be published world-wide). So on a Saturday afternoon with his four kids in tow, he set out to find a good area in Nashua’s Mine Falls Park and found a particularly well-suited spot. The site boasts a nice streamside location that gets little attention from muggles in this heavily-used park.&lt;/font&gt; &lt;a href="http://img.geocaching.com/cache/log/9bf670ff-d36c-432c-8a8f-a045def2cac1.jpg"&gt;&lt;font color="#0000FF" face="Calibri" size="4"&gt;Placing one Tupperware Container within a second one&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;font face="Calibri" size="4"&gt;(for added weatherability) he submitted the cache page and coords to Groundspeak. At that time there were no “local reviewers” and Jeremy Irish himself published the cache on October 29&lt;sup&gt;th&lt;/sup&gt;, which was then first found by&lt;/font&gt; &lt;a href="http://www.geocaching.com/seek/log.aspx?LUID=5460a1ae-48b4-431e-879a-54c75d52b334"&gt;&lt;font color="#0000FF" face="Calibri" size="4"&gt;BobHogan&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;font face="Calibri"&gt;&lt;font size="4"&gt;on December 24&lt;sup&gt;th&lt;/sup&gt;.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align:justify;margin:0in 0in 10pt;"&gt;&lt;font face="Calibri" size="4"&gt; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align:justify;margin:0in 0in 10pt;"&gt;&lt;font face="Calibri" size="4"&gt;Ironically, the person responsible for placing New Hampshire’s first cache, ultimately did little caching himself and by the time that NH#1- Mines Follies was about to turn ten, he had only logged three finds and had all but disappeared from the caching scene. With much searching over the course of about a year,&lt;/font&gt; &lt;a href="http://img.geocaching.com/cache/log/7ed96921-3d36-4c53-9a54-04f5d1fbb6e4.jpg"&gt;&lt;font color="#0000FF" face="Calibri" size="4"&gt;Paul (shown on left)&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;font face="Calibri" size="4"&gt;was finally contacted and agreed to turn over the cache to&lt;/font&gt; &lt;a href="http://www.geocaching.com/profile/?guid=0417b19a-3bbd-4580-b1f7-69591e158b34&amp;amp;wid=012677d1-77e0-4821-b2b3-d2ae46ea2b70&amp;amp;ds=2"&gt;&lt;font color="#0000FF" face="Calibri" size="4"&gt;Nashuan&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;font face="Calibri" size="4"&gt;. The original Tupperware containers had been muggled and with so many people coming to seek this one out, an&lt;/font&gt; &lt;a href="http://img.geocaching.com/cache/log/large/3d477b38-a62b-453f-a61a-ecbf29c84223.jpg"&gt;&lt;font color="#0000FF" face="Calibri" size="4"&gt;ammo can&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;font face="Calibri"&gt;&lt;font size="4"&gt;made for a better choice.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align:justify;margin:0in 0in 10pt;"&gt;&lt;font face="Calibri" size="4"&gt; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align:justify;margin:0in 0in 10pt;"&gt;&lt;font face="Calibri" size="4"&gt;A&lt;/font&gt; &lt;a href="http://coord.info/GC2G7G0"&gt;&lt;font color="#0000FF" face="Calibri" size="4"&gt;10-year anniversary event&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;font face="Calibri"&gt;&lt;font size="4"&gt;was held on 10/29/2010 and Nashuan had been in contact with Paul, hoping to have him as a surprise guest. Initially Paul agreed, but then emailed Nashuan about 45 minutes prior to the start of the event; saying that he would be tied up at work. This was disappointing news but the “show was to go on”. Seeing some 60 people milling about in the parking lot, there was one individual who seemed a little bit out of place and overwhelmed. Minutes later, he walked over to Nashuan and announced “I’m Paul”. Nashuan's heart about jumped out of his chest with elation to have Paul attend after all. He said that he was not expecting “this” and explained that he thought there might be perhaps a half dozen geocachers in attendance. In fact the event was scheduled for 4:45 PM on a Friday afternoon, so attendance was actually lower than what it should have been; but all that time Paul had no inkling as to what his original cache placement started in the state of New Hampshire.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align:justify;margin:0in 0in 10pt;"&gt;&lt;font face="Calibri" size="4"&gt; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align:justify;margin:0in 0in 10pt;"&gt;&lt;font face="Calibri"&gt;&lt;font size="4"&gt;When the transfer of the cache took place, Nashuan made a conscious decision to leave the page unaltered. There were no parking coords listed at the time, none of the several possible trailheads were given, and no hints on how to approach the cache were included with the listing. A rite of passage has developed over the years in that cachers had to work out how to get to the “right side of the stream”, and often mention whether or not they got it right. The exact location is tricky to find, which gave the cache much of its protection over the years. It is an oasis in a heavily used park.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align:justify;margin:0in 0in 10pt;"&gt;&lt;font face="Calibri" size="4"&gt; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align:justify;margin:0in 0in 10pt;"&gt;&lt;font face="Calibri"&gt;&lt;font size="4"&gt;Nashuan maintained the cache enthusiastically for over twelve years until deciding in 2022 that it was &lt;a href="https://coord.info/GL18F440R"&gt;&lt;font color="#0000FF" face="Calibri" size="4"&gt;time to pass maintenance responsibilities&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;font face="Calibri" size="4"&gt; to the &lt;a href="https://www.geocaching.com/profile/?guid=768245a7-5756-49fc-a17e-1b3210d17c23"&gt;&lt;font color="#0000FF" face="Calibri" size="4"&gt;solid-rock-seekers&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;font face="Calibri" size="4"&gt;, who had actually been unofficial maintainers for a few years from 2004-2006, including &lt;a href="https://coord.info/GL5RH2W"&gt;&lt;font color="#0000FF" face="Calibri" size="4"&gt;replacing the original logbook when it was needed on 8 September 2004&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;font face="Calibri" size="4"&gt;.

&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align:justify;margin:0in 0in 10pt;"&gt;&lt;font face="Calibri" size="4"&gt; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align:justify;margin:0in 0in 10pt;"&gt;&lt;font face="Calibri"&gt;&lt;font size="4"&gt;Thanks are due to Paul Lamere for his contribution to this game/sport/activity that we all participate in. He could have read the original Slashdot article and in finding no caches nearby simply moved on to some other interest. His initiative in placing New Hampshire’s first cache has brought challenge and wholesome enjoyment to over 1000 cachers to date and hopefully will endure for many years to come.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align:justify;margin:0in 0in 10pt;"&gt;&lt;font face="Calibri" size="4"&gt; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align:justify;margin:0in 0in 10pt;"&gt;&lt;font face="Calibri"&gt;&lt;font size="4"&gt;Below this string of stars is found the text as originally written by Paul to guide interested explorers to his cache:&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align:justify;margin:0in 0in 10pt;"&gt;&lt;font face="Calibri" size="4"&gt; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align:justify;margin:0in 0in 10pt;"&gt;&lt;font face="Calibri"&gt;&lt;font size="4"&gt;************************************************************************&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align:justify;margin:0in 0in 10pt;"&gt;&lt;font face="Calibri"&gt;&lt;font size="4"&gt;Difficulty: 2&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align:justify;margin:0in 0in 10pt;"&gt;&lt;font face="Calibri"&gt;&lt;font size="4"&gt;Terrain: 2&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align:justify;margin:0in 0in 10pt;"&gt;&lt;font face="Calibri"&gt;&lt;font size="4"&gt;This cache is on public land in a fairly urban setting, an easy walk from a parked car. Bring the kids. This is a fairly well travelled area so the cache is hidden such that it is not easy to see unless you are looking hard for it. I hope you don't get stumped. There are lots of geographic features in the area so you may find that even when you are close to the cache you "can't get there from here" so plan your route accordingly.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align:justify;margin:0in 0in 10pt;"&gt;&lt;font face="Calibri"&gt;&lt;font size="4"&gt;Since this is a rather well travelled area, please remember to re-hide the cache rather well, so it is only barely visible to the casual passerby.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align:justify;margin:0in 0in 10pt;"&gt;&lt;font face="Calibri"&gt;&lt;font size="4"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;November, 2003&lt;/strong&gt; - A maintenance visit ... checked to make sure all was ready for the winter ... it was.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align:justify;margin:0in 0in 10pt;"&gt;&lt;font face="Calibri"&gt;&lt;font size="4"&gt;Paul, Chris, Cari, Liz.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class="MsoNormal" style="text-align:justify;margin:0in 0in 10pt;"&gt;&lt;font face="Calibri"&gt; &lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;</groundspeak:long_description><groundspeak:encoded_hints>Looking down the stream, the cache is on the right bank.
If you still can't find it ... look for the fallen tree ... if you are still 'stumped' ... it must be gone!</groundspeak:encoded_hints><groundspeak:logs><groundspeak:log id="1364107376"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-28T19:59:25</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="55468191">TheGreatTACO</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Thanks for hiding the cache especially it was the first one, have a good day</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1364230787"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-28T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Write note</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="6692700">Arbion</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Stopped by for a visit with a wo Scout groups I was teaching about Geocaching.  TB left by one of these groups with a goal of visiting WV.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363957462"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-25T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="5445477">Albus_Birch</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Second cache of the day, still damp, but not as drizzly.  Found a good place to park and then the path, then my wife pointed out the off-shoot.  On our trek to the cache, we noticed a different connector path, of which we made a mental note.  

Backtracked a little to take a possible easier path to the final, which was correct.  Then, my wife spotted it before me.  

Yes, that connector path was a better choice for the return trip.  

Favorite point for bringing us to this park and for maintaining this oldie!

8046</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1363489871"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-25T10:18:44</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="8724011">Candy Apple 68</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">What a magnificent albeit soggy hike today!! Thanks for maintaining and giving us a reason to explore this beautiful area!  Greetings from Letchworth State Park in Mount Morris, NY :)</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="1362503088"><groundspeak:date>2026-05-21T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="44880844">cesium12</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">TFTC</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log><groundspeak:log id="463536310"><groundspeak:date>2014-11-26T12:00:00</groundspeak:date><groundspeak:type>Found it</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:finder id="2089726">travelingGeek</groundspeak:finder><groundspeak:text encoded="false">Great find!   We were going to drive from Scranton, PA to Tyngsboro, Ma but the dire predictions of snow an traffic had me worried since we were down to just one driver (me) and I usually avoid that kind of long drive on a sunny day!

Quick check of the airlines showed $700 each for a one way, but only 10K points.... That is why I save my points whenever I can... easy decision to take the 6:03 from Scranton.  It was still dark and dry when we got to Newark and had just begun to drizzle when we got to Manchester at 9am.

The downside to avoiding all the traffic and drive time was all the great geocaches we had to pass up.  Fortunately, I knew there was this super special cache to find after leaving the airport.  I already had this month on Jasmer, but who can pass up such an old cache and the First and Oldest Active in New Hampshire was an awesome bonus!  

Awesome park and I'd love to spend more time here on a future trip.

Thanks for maintain this one so well!  loved the hide and field hints around it and even spotted a big turtle shell near by.  Dropped of a traveler I had with me for a world tour.
Found with ThePaperPilot and PuzzlePainter.</groundspeak:text></groundspeak:log></groundspeak:logs></groundspeak:cache></wpt><wpt lat="41.093833" lon="-74.203"><time>2000-11-25T00:00:00</time><name>GCC8</name><desc>gerbiL cacHe by cach=e_ninjA</desc><url>https://www.geocaching.com/geocache/GCC8</url><urlname>gerbiL cacHe</urlname><sym>Geocache</sym><type>Geocache|Traditional Cache</type><groundspeak:cache id="200" available="true" archived="false"><groundspeak:name>gerbiL cacHe</groundspeak:name><groundspeak:placed_by>cach=e_ninjA</groundspeak:placed_by><groundspeak:owner id="695">cache_ninja</groundspeak:owner><groundspeak:type>Traditional Cache</groundspeak:type><groundspeak:container>Other</groundspeak:container><groundspeak:attributes /><groundspeak:difficulty>2</groundspeak:difficulty><groundspeak:terrain>2</groundspeak:terrain><groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country><groundspeak:state>New Jersey</groundspeak:state><groundspeak:short_description>1st cache in the Gar^den S#Tat@E?!! thinK so.</groundspeak:short_description><groundspeak:long_description>terrAin/dif=ficulty 2/2 , eaSy hikinG trAils, buT some ROcks and
hilLY, miNima L n"0vice climbINg requiRed to finD i%t. 
